00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:21.400 position:35% line:83% align:start
[REPORTER]
We have a follow-up report

00:03:21.433 --> 00:03:23.002 position:33% line:83% align:start
from live at
the scene of today's

00:03:23.035 --> 00:03:25.371 position:21% line:83% align:start
armed occupation of
the Far East Trade Embassy.

00:03:25.404 --> 00:03:28.240 position:16% line:83% align:start
Sources say there are 42
hostages being held by 11...

00:03:28.274 --> 00:03:32.311 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're clearly the right woman
for the job, Major Kusanagi.

00:03:32.344 --> 00:03:37.549 position:13% line:83% align:start
That is very kind of you,
Mister Fujimoto.

00:03:37.583 --> 00:03:41.320 position:21% line:83% align:start
Our victory is close
at hand, Lt. Colonel.

00:03:41.353 --> 00:03:44.490 position:27% line:83% align:start
Let us hope so,
Ambassador Wong.

00:03:48.127 --> 00:03:51.530 position:19% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] The interview
is merely a formality.

00:03:51.563 --> 00:03:53.932 position:19% line:83% align:start
The council functions
are performed by AI.

00:03:53.966 --> 00:03:56.001 position:10% line:89% align:start
How the times have changed.

00:03:56.035 --> 00:03:58.404 position:21% line:83% align:start
But this AI will be
listening in, I presume.

00:03:58.437 --> 00:04:03.575 position:19% line:83% align:start
There's no need to be
intimidated by a machine.

00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:05.277 position:24% line:89% align:start
We have a problem,

00:04:05.311 --> 00:04:08.581 position:13% line:83% align:start
and your unit can provide
the perfect solution.

00:04:15.521 --> 00:04:17.624 position:16% line:89% align:start
[HOSTAGES scream, gasp]

00:04:17.657 --> 00:04:20.159 position:10% line:83% align:start
[KURUTSU] The world entered
a rapid era of change

00:04:20.192 --> 00:04:22.194 position:21% line:89% align:start
after the war ended.

00:04:22.227 --> 00:04:25.230 position:24% line:83% align:start
This country is no
exception, of course.

00:04:28.167 --> 00:04:30.069 position:10% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] The war accelerated
both cyberbrain

00:04:30.102 --> 00:04:31.604 position:10% line:89% align:start
and prosthetic development.

00:04:31.638 --> 00:04:35.240 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course, the cybercrimes born
of such technology are serious,

00:04:35.274 --> 00:04:38.911 position:13% line:83% align:start
but they're only a symptom
of another problem.

00:04:41.914 --> 00:04:44.116 position:21% line:83% align:start
Between cyberbrains
and prosthetics,

00:04:44.149 --> 00:04:46.385 position:16% line:83% align:start
we're seeing the largest
profit-seeking system

00:04:46.418 --> 00:04:48.253 position:10% line:89% align:start
in the history of the world.

00:04:48.287 --> 00:04:49.922 position:13% line:83% align:start
And that means the amount
of data shared

00:04:49.955 --> 00:04:51.390 position:10% line:89% align:start
in real time is staggering;

00:04:51.423 --> 00:04:53.459 position:13% line:83% align:start
it's gone far beyond what
any government in the world

00:04:53.493 --> 00:04:55.495 position:16% line:89% align:start
is capable of managing.

00:04:59.164 --> 00:05:01.967 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] But even assuming that
business conglomerates eliminate

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.069 position:5% line:89% align:start
the concept of nations one day,

00:05:04.103 --> 00:05:07.239 position:5% line:83% align:start
that doesn't mean that the state
is without a purpose.

00:05:07.272 --> 00:05:09.408 position:13% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] The global economy
that's taking over today

00:05:09.441 --> 00:05:11.410 position:30% line:83% align:start
breeds nothing
but anarchy.

00:05:11.443 --> 00:05:15.548 position:7% line:83% align:start
It puts the financial security
of all private citizens at risk.

00:05:15.582 --> 00:05:18.984 position:21% line:83% align:start
The state must exist
to uphold their welfare.

00:05:19.017 --> 00:05:20.520 position:30% line:83% align:start
[COP A gasps]
Fall back!

00:05:34.032 --> 00:05:36.068 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KURUTSU] Cyberbrains and
prosthetics have formed

00:05:36.101 --> 00:05:37.202 position:19% line:89% align:start
an unbreakable bridge

00:05:37.236 --> 00:05:40.507 position:7% line:83% align:start
between the munitions industry
and household economics.

00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:44.109 position:13% line:83% align:start
No government regulations
can change that or stop it.

00:05:44.143 --> 00:05:46.646 position:21% line:89% align:start
[keyboard clacking]

00:05:46.679 --> 00:05:48.515 position:16% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] While it's true
that no executive body

00:05:48.548 --> 00:05:50.115 position:16% line:89% align:start
can contain the system,

00:05:50.149 --> 00:05:52.284 position:19% line:83% align:start
that doesn't mean that
it transcends the laws

00:05:52.317 --> 00:05:54.186 position:13% line:89% align:start
established by the state.

00:05:55.655 --> 00:05:57.322 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Systems which break the rules

00:05:57.357 --> 00:06:01.561 position:5% line:83% align:start
must be dealt with accordingly,
regardless of their influence.

00:06:04.764 --> 00:06:07.600 position:21% line:83% align:start
Sharing information,
gives us two choices:

00:06:07.634 --> 00:06:11.136 position:13% line:83% align:start
submitting to the system,
or becoming part of it.

00:06:11.170 --> 00:06:13.506 position:21% line:89% align:start
What we need now...

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:17.477 position:16% line:83% align:start
...is an executive force
to keep the system in line.

00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:19.412 position:10% line:89% align:start
...is an integrated network,

00:06:19.446 --> 00:06:22.515 position:10% line:83% align:start
one that sorts people within
the system appropriately.

00:06:26.419 --> 00:06:28.220 position:35% line:83% align:start
[RICHARD]
Hm.

00:06:28.253 --> 00:06:30.055 position:27% line:89% align:start
A lovely speech.

00:06:30.088 --> 00:06:31.691 position:27% line:83% align:start
And don't worry,
Lieutenant Colonel,

00:06:31.724 --> 00:06:33.593 position:27% line:83% align:start
we recognize you
and your organization

00:06:33.626 --> 00:06:35.595 position:7% line:89% align:start
as a most welcome enterprise.

00:06:35.628 --> 00:06:37.697 position:7% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] Government authorized
cyber investigations

00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:39.499 position:10% line:89% align:start
and anti-terror activities.

00:06:39.532 --> 00:06:43.035 position:13% line:83% align:start
The power to bring charges
for corporate crimes.

00:06:43.068 --> 00:06:47.039 position:19% line:83% align:start
Nothing will be taboo
for your unit.

00:06:47.072 --> 00:06:48.408 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
You done yet, Major?

00:06:48.441 --> 00:06:50.209 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
In a moment.

00:06:50.242 --> 00:06:51.678 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's the sitrep?

00:06:51.711 --> 00:06:53.480 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Aside from
the raid going on,

00:06:53.513 --> 00:06:56.416 position:24% line:83% align:start
everyone's having
a jolly old time.

00:06:58.050 --> 00:06:59.486 position:27% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Dammit!
Ape-Face from Section 9

00:06:59.519 --> 00:07:01.554 position:33% line:83% align:start
is sticking
his nose in again.

00:07:04.357 --> 00:07:05.758 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Why is that a problem?

00:07:05.792 --> 00:07:08.561 position:16% line:83% align:start
Chief Aramaki is the one
who requested us, right?

00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:11.364 position:10% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] That means he wants
us working under him.

00:07:11.397 --> 00:07:14.400 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] And there's no way
that'll fly with our leader.

00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.035 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] The ape's assumed
authority over the situation.

00:07:17.069 --> 00:07:18.304 position:27% line:89% align:start
What now, Major?

00:07:18.338 --> 00:07:20.240 position:19% line:83% align:start
Want me to break into
Section 9's net?

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.674 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
I'll negotiate with him.

00:07:21.708 --> 00:07:23.543 position:24% line:89% align:start
Stand by for now.

00:07:28.181 --> 00:07:29.516 position:24% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] My father,
the Prime Minister,

00:07:29.549 --> 00:07:33.319 position:5% line:83% align:start
would like to see this incident
resolved promptly.

00:07:33.353 --> 00:07:35.655 position:24% line:83% align:start
And now, you have
your authority.

00:07:35.688 --> 00:07:38.157 position:7% line:89% align:start
The hard part will come next.

00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:40.793 position:13% line:89% align:start
You will not regret this.

00:07:40.827 --> 00:07:42.762 position:27% line:89% align:start
Thank you, sir.

00:07:46.699 --> 00:07:50.436 position:24% line:83% align:start
Would you say that
you love this country?

00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.472 position:21% line:83% align:start
Enough to give this
mission my full attention,

00:07:52.505 --> 00:07:53.706 position:16% line:89% align:start
if that's what you mean.

00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:54.707 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Hm.

00:07:54.741 --> 00:07:56.743 position:13% line:83% align:start
Then it seems this country
should try harder

00:07:56.776 --> 00:07:58.678 position:16% line:89% align:start
to earn your affection.

00:07:58.711 --> 00:08:00.413 position:24% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO chuckles]

00:08:00.446 --> 00:08:03.316 position:35% line:83% align:start
Well then,
I'll get to work.

00:08:05.151 --> 00:08:06.719 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
One last thing.

00:08:06.753 --> 00:08:08.086 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Huh?

00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:13.660 position:7% line:89% align:start
Your smile is too calculated.

00:08:13.693 --> 00:08:17.864 position:5% line:83% align:start
You don't need to devote so much
of your prosthetic memory to it.

00:08:17.897 --> 00:08:21.434 position:7% line:83% align:start
I assure you, I've never given
a programmed smile in my life.

00:08:21.467 --> 00:08:23.636 position:35% line:89% align:start
It's real.

00:08:23.670 --> 00:08:24.437 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Hm.

00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:26.439 position:30% line:89% align:start
If you say so.

00:08:26.472 --> 00:08:28.808 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'll trust your Ghost
on this one.

00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:33.546 position:13% line:89% align:start
I won't let you down, sir.

00:08:42.722 --> 00:08:44.490 position:35% line:89% align:start
Good luck.

00:08:50.496 --> 00:08:52.398 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Ishikawa, information.

00:08:52.432 --> 00:08:53.600 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
I'm seeing a report

00:08:53.633 --> 00:08:56.869 position:5% line:83% align:start
from the federal council session
320 approving our budget.

00:08:56.903 --> 00:08:59.572 position:24% line:89% align:start
Nice work, Major.

00:09:01.608 --> 00:09:02.709 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Get in my lobby.

00:09:02.742 --> 00:09:05.378 position:30% line:83% align:start
We're starting
the case now.

00:09:29.335 --> 00:09:32.940 position:13% line:83% align:start
Kusanagi, I didn't expect
to see you here.

00:09:32.973 --> 00:09:37.243 position:13% line:83% align:start
Come to wag your tail for
our antiquated government?

00:09:37.276 --> 00:09:38.277 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
I don't know.

00:09:38.311 --> 00:09:39.479 position:13% line:83% align:start
Have you come to sell out
to some corporation,

00:09:39.512 --> 00:09:42.849 position:10% line:83% align:start
so you can make an easy buck
on the backs of our people?

00:09:42.882 --> 00:09:45.818 position:16% line:83% align:start
Most of the military is
going to become privatized.

00:09:45.852 --> 00:09:47.054 position:16% line:89% align:start
If you're going to war,

00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:50.523 position:10% line:83% align:start
you should at least have the
sense to side with the winners.

00:09:50.556 --> 00:09:53.359 position:16% line:83% align:start
The war is already over,
and it wasn't fought

00:09:53.393 --> 00:09:57.697 position:13% line:83% align:start
so that someone could put
a serial number on my Ghost.

00:09:57.730 --> 00:10:01.567 position:16% line:83% align:start
Everyone, is replaceable
and expendable.

00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:04.872 position:7% line:83% align:start
Now let's see which one of us
is disposable, too.

00:10:04.905 --> 00:10:07.173 position:27% line:89% align:start
We'll find out.

00:10:30.763 --> 00:10:32.298 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
ETA is seven minutes.

00:10:32.331 --> 00:10:34.567 position:13% line:89% align:start
I assume you have my info?

00:10:52.719 --> 00:10:54.687 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Eleven soldiers
who opposed downgrading

00:10:54.721 --> 00:10:57.724 position:13% line:83% align:start
the Ministry of Defense to
"Defense Agency" have occupied

00:10:57.758 --> 00:11:02.395 position:16% line:83% align:start
the East Asian Economic
Federation's trade embassy.

00:11:02.428 --> 00:11:03.696 position:30% line:83% align:start
Here are their
current positions,

00:11:03.730 --> 00:11:07.400 position:27% line:83% align:start
backgrounds, and
associated organizations.

00:11:07.433 --> 00:11:09.302 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Uh-huhhhh.

00:11:09.335 --> 00:11:12.305 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Heh. All eleven
are prosthetized,

00:11:12.338 --> 00:11:15.408 position:5% line:83% align:start
and two of 'em have heavy-class
converted prosthetics.

00:11:15.441 --> 00:11:18.979 position:5% line:83% align:start
In other words, the riot police
aren't looking so hot.

00:11:21.782 --> 00:11:23.649 position:10% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] Out of 42 hostages
it looks like

00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:27.386 position:10% line:83% align:start
36 are confined in the hall
with the bombs.

00:11:27.420 --> 00:11:30.656 position:10% line:83% align:start
The other six are higher-ups
who escaped into the panic room.

00:11:30.691 --> 00:11:32.960 position:27% line:83% align:start
They're probably
the real targets.

00:11:32.993 --> 00:11:35.361 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] We're screwed
if they open that door.

00:11:35.394 --> 00:11:36.964 position:19% line:83% align:start
They'll either hole up
in there for months

00:11:36.997 --> 00:11:39.833 position:27% line:83% align:start
or start staging
public executions.

00:11:39.867 --> 00:11:41.434 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
What are their demands?

00:11:41.467 --> 00:11:43.369 position:7% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] They want the government
to keep the Ministry

00:11:43.402 --> 00:11:44.972 position:10% line:89% align:start
and suspend military trials.

00:11:45.005 --> 00:11:47.074 position:19% line:83% align:start
They don't care about
their own safety.

00:11:47.107 --> 00:11:48.208 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
If they want to make

00:11:48.242 --> 00:11:50.944 position:16% line:83% align:start
a little battlefield for
themselves, we'll indulge them.

00:11:50.978 --> 00:11:53.080 position:5% line:89% align:start
Execute Domination on my signal.

00:11:53.113 --> 00:11:54.580 position:27% line:89% align:start
We're going in.

00:11:54.614 --> 00:11:57.017 position:30% line:83% align:start
Are you nuts?
Just the seven of us?

00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.052 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] We've got a sniper,
cyberbrain hacking,

00:11:59.086 --> 00:12:01.054 position:5% line:89% align:start
and Logicoma to act as shields.

00:12:01.088 --> 00:12:02.823 position:19% line:83% align:start
The riot police at the
perimeter will keep away

00:12:02.856 --> 00:12:04.658 position:7% line:89% align:start
any potential reinforcements.

00:12:04.691 --> 00:12:05.391 position:33% line:89% align:start
We're fine.

00:12:05.424 --> 00:12:07.795 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Hmmph. You are the boss.

00:12:07.828 --> 00:12:10.063 position:10% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Too bad this mission
doesn't call for ugly suits

00:12:10.097 --> 00:12:11.799 position:5% line:89% align:start
and old-fashioned neckties, huh?

00:12:11.832 --> 00:12:13.066 position:27% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA groans]

00:12:13.100 --> 00:12:15.368 position:7% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] Must be rough, being the
only one with a natural body.

00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:17.704 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why not take this chance
to go full cyborg?

00:12:17.738 --> 00:12:18.404 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA gasps]

00:12:18.437 --> 00:12:19.405 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
It'd be a real pity

00:12:19.438 --> 00:12:22.341 position:16% line:83% align:start
to leave that beautiful
wife of yours a widow.

00:12:22.375 --> 00:12:24.978 position:5% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Don't worry, I'll be
sure to collect your last words

00:12:25.012 --> 00:12:27.513 position:19% line:83% align:start
before your cyberbrain
gets blown away.

00:12:27.547 --> 00:12:29.616 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAITO] And if you happen
to get tortured by the enemy,

00:12:29.650 --> 00:12:32.385 position:16% line:83% align:start
I can be the one to end
your suffering for you.

00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:34.520 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] Y'know what?
Screw you guys!

00:12:34.554 --> 00:12:36.790 position:19% line:89% align:start
Let's go! I got this!

00:12:36.824 --> 00:12:38.125 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I brought you together
because you're all

00:12:38.158 --> 00:12:41.128 position:27% line:83% align:start
top-notch parts
in your own right.

00:12:41.161 --> 00:12:44.898 position:13% line:83% align:start
Still, like any part, I'll
purge you if you can't perform.

00:12:44.932 --> 00:12:47.634 position:7% line:83% align:start
So you can act like a bunch of
jackasses if you like,

00:12:47.668 --> 00:12:49.069 position:19% line:83% align:start
but most of you would
either be in jail

00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:50.403 position:13% line:89% align:start
or end up shot in the back

00:12:50.436 --> 00:12:53.674 position:16% line:83% align:start
if I didn't recruit you
for this squad.

00:12:53.707 --> 00:12:56.009 position:24% line:89% align:start
Don't forget that.

00:12:56.043 --> 00:12:59.378 position:24% line:83% align:start
Get into position.
It's time to move.

00:13:00.848 --> 00:13:03.917 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] So we're just
parts of a machine now?

00:13:03.951 --> 00:13:05.819 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] I wouldn't
take it personally.

00:13:05.853 --> 00:13:09.156 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm sure our darling princess
meant that as a pep talk.

00:13:09.189 --> 00:13:10.624 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
She's a monster.

00:13:10.657 --> 00:13:12.059 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
A gorilla woman.

00:13:12.092 --> 00:13:14.161 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
She's gonna replace us.

00:13:14.194 --> 00:13:17.531 position:19% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] Just do the job,
we'll be fine.

00:13:17.564 --> 00:13:19.432 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Speak for yourself.

00:13:19.465 --> 00:13:22.035 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna die
for sure out there.

00:13:22.069 --> 00:13:25.072 position:7% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] We can't storm them
without more personnel!

00:13:25.105 --> 00:13:28.709 position:19% line:83% align:start
Where are the Rangers?
Or The Special Forces?

00:13:28.742 --> 00:13:30.510 position:30% line:83% align:start
[SUBORDINATE]
They all refused the job.

00:13:30.544 --> 00:13:32.012 position:19% line:83% align:start
Said they didn't want
to shoot their own people

00:13:32.045 --> 00:13:34.982 position:21% line:83% align:start
to save some foreign
war merchants.

00:13:35.015 --> 00:13:36.583 position:24% line:83% align:start
If they care about
