00:26:42.504 --> 00:26:43.838 position:30% line:89% align:start
[SAITO growls]

00:26:43.873 --> 00:26:45.407 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] So that leaves
me and the rookie

00:26:45.440 --> 00:26:46.808 position:16% line:89% align:start
to track the perps, huh?

00:26:46.841 --> 00:26:49.711 position:16% line:83% align:start
They're probably halfway
around the world by now.

00:26:49.744 --> 00:26:52.213 position:5% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] Nah, if they're trying to
mess with domestic affairs,

00:26:52.247 --> 00:26:53.682 position:19% line:83% align:start
they've got operatives
in our government

00:26:53.715 --> 00:26:55.316 position:13% line:89% align:start
who can't move right away.

00:26:55.350 --> 00:26:57.887 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] In which case,
there's probably a third party,

00:26:57.920 --> 00:27:00.822 position:10% line:83% align:start
someone who used these guys
and then iced them.

00:27:00.856 --> 00:27:03.358 position:19% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Let's hope
they're foreigners this time.

00:27:03.391 --> 00:27:05.527 position:13% line:83% align:start
I've had enough of killing
my own countrymen.

00:27:05.560 --> 00:27:07.830 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Do background checks
on everyone you see,

00:27:07.863 --> 00:27:10.866 position:7% line:83% align:start
and stay out of confrontations
with other spies.

00:27:14.937 --> 00:27:17.739 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Special Advisor Fujimoto.

00:27:23.712 --> 00:27:26.748 position:13% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] I came for the DNA
testing on his body.

00:27:26.782 --> 00:27:30.953 position:10% line:83% align:start
You can't even tell he's my
father by looking at him now.

00:27:30.986 --> 00:27:33.956 position:21% line:83% align:start
For what it's worth,
I will find the culprit.

00:27:33.989 --> 00:27:35.724 position:19% line:89% align:start
My mind's so mixed up.

00:27:35.757 --> 00:27:36.725 position:16% line:89% align:start
When they questioned me,

00:27:36.758 --> 00:27:39.461 position:16% line:83% align:start
I couldn't even remember
what happened yesterday.

00:27:39.494 --> 00:27:42.664 position:16% line:83% align:start
Let alone the last thing
I spoke to him about.

00:27:42.697 --> 00:27:44.632 position:7% line:89% align:start
I went through the same thing.

00:27:44.666 --> 00:27:46.468 position:27% line:89% align:start
During the war.

00:27:46.501 --> 00:27:49.872 position:24% line:83% align:start
Did your memories
ever come back?

00:27:49.905 --> 00:27:51.506 position:24% line:89% align:start
Every single one.

00:27:51.539 --> 00:27:54.442 position:13% line:89% align:start
And I won't forget again.

00:27:58.948 --> 00:28:00.348 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Right before he died,

00:28:00.381 --> 00:28:03.052 position:19% line:83% align:start
he issued some sort of
directive to me.

00:28:03.085 --> 00:28:05.620 position:10% line:83% align:start
Unfortunately, it seems that
someone jammed the signal

00:28:05.653 --> 00:28:07.589 position:13% line:89% align:start
and it didn't get through.

00:28:11.593 --> 00:28:12.828 position:38% line:89% align:start
Please.

00:28:12.862 --> 00:28:15.931 position:24% line:83% align:start
At the very least,
find out his final message.

00:28:15.965 --> 00:28:17.833 position:27% line:89% align:start
I have to know.

00:28:21.669 --> 00:28:23.005 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Oh, and...

00:28:23.038 --> 00:28:24.673 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes?

00:28:24.707 --> 00:28:27.375 position:19% line:83% align:start
Do you think we could
have dinner sometime?

00:28:27.408 --> 00:28:28.343 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Uh...

00:28:28.376 --> 00:28:32.647 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'd like to talk...
and not about business.

00:28:32.681 --> 00:28:33.983 position:27% line:83% align:start
There aren't too
many restaurants

00:28:34.016 --> 00:28:35.851 position:19% line:89% align:start
I can go to, you know.

00:28:45.027 --> 00:28:46.829 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Ishikawa, I assume you heard?

00:28:46.862 --> 00:28:49.297 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Yeah. I'm on it.

00:28:58.841 --> 00:29:00.643 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Want me to keep tabs on him?

00:29:00.676 --> 00:29:02.343 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Just get their
Net like I told you to

00:29:02.377 --> 00:29:04.379 position:10% line:89% align:start
and mind your own business.

00:29:04.412 --> 00:29:06.715 position:19% line:83% align:start
What's he doing trying
to pick up girls anyway?

00:29:06.749 --> 00:29:08.083 position:24% line:89% align:start
His dad just died!

00:29:08.117 --> 00:29:09.785 position:19% line:89% align:start
And the Major? Really?

00:29:09.819 --> 00:29:11.821 position:30% line:83% align:start
It was prob'ly
love at first sight.

00:29:11.854 --> 00:29:13.722 position:27% line:83% align:start
He's a rich boy
politician's son,

00:29:13.756 --> 00:29:16.391 position:21% line:83% align:start
so he doesn't get to
meet her type every day.

00:29:16.424 --> 00:29:18.727 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's better to focus
on the job, right?

00:29:18.761 --> 00:29:20.696 position:16% line:89% align:start
Enjoy our new authority?

00:29:33.742 --> 00:29:35.144 position:24% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
It's been 900 hours

00:29:35.177 --> 00:29:36.979 position:7% line:89% align:start
since I last saw someone move.

00:29:37.012 --> 00:29:39.915 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I heard that Unit 501
had been privatized,

00:29:39.949 --> 00:29:42.718 position:16% line:83% align:start
but I didn't realize it
was an automated factory.

00:29:42.751 --> 00:29:44.920 position:5% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] Everyone went
to work for Harimadara.

00:29:44.954 --> 00:29:48.824 position:24% line:83% align:start
What do you need?
A tour of the place?

00:29:48.858 --> 00:29:51.861 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do you know why Kurutsu
was at that meeting?

00:29:51.894 --> 00:29:54.429 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
For profit and for survival.

00:29:54.462 --> 00:29:57.032 position:13% line:83% align:start
Ambassador Wong and the PM
were working on an agreement

00:29:57.066 --> 00:29:59.467 position:16% line:83% align:start
to avoid any prosthetics
development dead-ends.

00:29:59.501 --> 00:30:01.670 position:7% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] The idea was
to keep production lines going

00:30:01.704 --> 00:30:04.139 position:10% line:83% align:start
by delaying the introduction
of new technology.

00:30:04.173 --> 00:30:05.107 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Why would you want to do that

00:30:05.140 --> 00:30:07.408 position:21% line:83% align:start
when the government
provides research grants

00:30:07.442 --> 00:30:09.478 position:10% line:89% align:start
to keep development moving?

00:30:09.511 --> 00:30:10.679 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
That sounds nice in theory,

00:30:10.713 --> 00:30:13.549 position:5% line:83% align:start
but the technology is advancing
too quickly to be utilized

00:30:13.582 --> 00:30:15.484 position:13% line:89% align:start
by the current generation.

00:30:15.517 --> 00:30:19.688 position:21% line:83% align:start
Others weren't made
full-cyborg at birth like you.

00:30:19.722 --> 00:30:22.091 position:19% line:83% align:start
Dr. Kusanagi developed
your body with the concept

00:30:22.124 --> 00:30:23.659 position:35% line:83% align:start
of future
growth in mind.

00:30:23.692 --> 00:30:25.661 position:24% line:83% align:start
Rather insightful
of him, really.

00:30:25.694 --> 00:30:29.031 position:10% line:83% align:start
So what you're in here doing
is making parts, is that it?

00:30:29.064 --> 00:30:31.667 position:24% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
Have to stay alive somehow.

00:30:31.700 --> 00:30:32.902 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
Technology conservation

00:30:32.935 --> 00:30:36.038 position:5% line:83% align:start
keeps numerous interests going,
but a technology revolution

00:30:36.071 --> 00:30:39.008 position:13% line:83% align:start
gives one group control of
an enormous market share.

00:30:39.041 --> 00:30:42.711 position:13% line:83% align:start
Kurutsu bet on the former
and was crushed by the latter.

00:30:43.746 --> 00:30:45.614 position:24% line:83% align:start
That would provide
a strong motive

00:30:45.648 --> 00:30:47.082 position:21% line:83% align:start
for the perp to kill
the ambassador

00:30:47.116 --> 00:30:50.419 position:19% line:83% align:start
and the Prime Minister
in the same hit.

00:30:51.887 --> 00:30:53.455 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Thanks for the information.

00:30:53.489 --> 00:30:55.691 position:10% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] You should
say hello to your parents.

00:30:55.724 --> 00:30:56.992 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Another time.

00:30:57.026 --> 00:30:58.661 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
Come whenever you like.

00:30:58.694 --> 00:31:01.463 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's not as though they'll
be going anywhere.

00:31:01.497 --> 00:31:03.432 position:19% line:89% align:start
The same goes for us.

00:31:06.201 --> 00:31:07.269 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Koichi Sawada,

00:31:07.303 --> 00:31:10.172 position:10% line:83% align:start
formerly an armored division
signal man in the Army.

00:31:10.205 --> 00:31:12.875 position:5% line:83% align:start
You really think a military Net
admin would hole up here?

00:31:12.908 --> 00:31:15.044 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] The perps had
the info in the access logs

00:31:15.077 --> 00:31:17.813 position:7% line:89% align:start
of their cyberbrains, so yeah.

00:31:21.951 --> 00:31:23.252 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Logicoma.

00:31:23.285 --> 00:31:26.155 position:16% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A] I only see
one heat signature.

00:31:26.188 --> 00:31:27.990 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
And no corpses, huh?

00:31:28.023 --> 00:31:30.059 position:19% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A] I can't
determine that from here.

00:31:30.092 --> 00:31:33.195 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Like they say,
dead men tell no tales,

00:31:33.228 --> 00:31:37.166 position:10% line:83% align:start
so if he ain't alive, we're
right back where we started.

00:31:52.848 --> 00:31:55.084 position:16% line:89% align:start
I have uninvited guests.

00:31:56.819 --> 00:31:59.054 position:27% line:83% align:start
Better shut your
door next time.

00:31:59.088 --> 00:32:02.024 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA sighs]

00:32:02.057 --> 00:32:04.960 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA] I thought someone
might come to speak with me.

00:32:04.994 --> 00:32:06.296 position:10% line:89% align:start
Just tell me what you need.

00:32:06.329 --> 00:32:08.197 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
You must be Koichi Sawada.

00:32:08.231 --> 00:32:09.631 position:16% line:89% align:start
We're sorry to intrude.

00:32:09.665 --> 00:32:12.768 position:16% line:83% align:start
We'd like to talk about
the PM's assassination.

00:32:17.039 --> 00:32:18.107 position:16% line:89% align:start
What's that data about?

00:32:18.140 --> 00:32:20.576 position:30% line:83% align:start
Think of them
as last words.

00:32:20.609 --> 00:32:22.245 position:13% line:89% align:start
My comrades had no money,

00:32:22.278 --> 00:32:25.315 position:16% line:83% align:start
so all they could leave
behind was a message.

00:32:25.348 --> 00:32:28.117 position:7% line:83% align:start
They're programmed to be sent
when they take their lives.

00:32:28.150 --> 00:32:30.186 position:21% line:83% align:start
And since they don't
have any family either,

00:32:30.220 --> 00:32:32.588 position:19% line:83% align:start
they have their final
testament sent to me--

00:32:32.621 --> 00:32:35.024 position:27% line:83% align:start
an administrator
they've never even met.

00:32:35.057 --> 00:32:37.559 position:19% line:83% align:start
I wish they'd at least
come speak to me first.

00:32:37.593 --> 00:32:40.230 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
So somebody did die?

00:32:40.263 --> 00:32:42.865 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Somewhere out there, yeah.

00:32:42.898 --> 00:32:44.633 position:13% line:89% align:start
Anyway, stand by for now.

00:32:44.666 --> 00:32:45.901 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Okay!

00:32:45.934 --> 00:32:49.772 position:5% line:83% align:start
[coughs] Was there ever mention
of killing the Prime Minister?

00:32:49.805 --> 00:32:51.106 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA]
Not at all.

00:32:51.141 --> 00:32:53.243 position:21% line:83% align:start
I do have the final
testaments of the men

00:32:53.276 --> 00:32:55.077 position:27% line:83% align:start
who occupied the
embassy, though.

00:32:56.712 --> 00:32:58.680 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] Are there any
you've lost contact with?

00:32:58.714 --> 00:33:01.617 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA]
Plenty. I'll forward you a list.

00:33:01.650 --> 00:33:03.786 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] And one you think
could be the ringleader?

00:33:03.819 --> 00:33:05.288 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA]
Colonel Haruyoshi Nada

00:33:05.321 --> 00:33:07.257 position:21% line:83% align:start
would probably have
the most clout.

00:33:07.290 --> 00:33:10.126 position:13% line:83% align:start
He was an informal advisor
to Vice-Minister Kitahara,

00:33:10.160 --> 00:33:13.263 position:24% line:83% align:start
but he disappeared
before the incident.

00:33:16.366 --> 00:33:19.701 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you're feeling down,
you can come by and talk, too.

00:33:19.735 --> 00:33:21.237 position:21% line:89% align:start
What does that mean?

00:33:21.271 --> 00:33:24.606 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA] Full cyborgs are at
the highest risk for suicide.

00:33:24.640 --> 00:33:26.309 position:10% line:89% align:start
Production standards change.

00:33:26.342 --> 00:33:28.043 position:10% line:89% align:start
Their old parts deteriorate,

00:33:28.078 --> 00:33:30.646 position:13% line:83% align:start
but they aren't compatible
with new tech.

00:33:33.083 --> 00:33:34.616 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA gasps]

00:33:35.818 --> 00:33:39.089 position:33% line:83% align:start
This is what
that looks like.

00:33:39.122 --> 00:33:41.757 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm grateful I can
work as a relay point.

00:33:41.790 --> 00:33:45.328 position:19% line:83% align:start
Otherwise, I'd likely
end up just like them.

00:33:47.796 --> 00:33:49.698 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SAWADA] If the cyberbrain
version you choose

00:33:49.731 --> 00:33:51.301 position:27% line:83% align:start
doesn't fit the
tide of the times,

00:33:51.334 --> 00:33:54.002 position:21% line:83% align:start
then prosthetization
dooms you...

00:33:54.037 --> 00:33:55.938 position:33% line:89% align:start
...to this.

00:34:01.177 --> 00:34:03.146 position:7% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A] What did you do
with the dead person?

00:34:03.179 --> 00:34:05.148 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
We couldn't do anything.

00:34:05.181 --> 00:34:06.349 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
If he can't be repaired,

00:34:06.382 --> 00:34:09.986 position:10% line:83% align:start
then I recommend recovering
his data for transfer later!

00:34:10.019 --> 00:34:13.323 position:10% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] If his body's dead,
his Ghost dies with it.

00:34:13.356 --> 00:34:15.391 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Well, that's just poor design!

00:34:15.425 --> 00:34:17.860 position:27% line:83% align:start
Batou, have you
ever died before?

00:34:19.162 --> 00:34:20.163 position:24% line:89% align:start
I was supposed to,

00:34:20.196 --> 00:34:23.299 position:10% line:83% align:start
but I ended up a full cyborg
like this instead.

00:34:23.333 --> 00:34:25.335 position:5% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A] Is that why you're
one of the Major's parts now--

00:34:25.368 --> 00:34:27.669 position:16% line:83% align:start
So you can keep working
till you die for real?

00:34:27.703 --> 00:34:30.106 position:19% line:89% align:start
Will you cut it out?!

00:34:30.140 --> 00:34:31.773 position:27% line:89% align:start
[BATOU chuckles]

00:34:31.807 --> 00:34:34.310 position:21% line:83% align:start
A stud like me isn't
goin' down that easily.

00:34:34.344 --> 00:34:36.379 position:24% line:89% align:start
Not yet. You hear?

00:34:36.412 --> 00:34:37.514 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Loud and clear!

00:34:37.547 --> 00:34:41.683 position:19% line:83% align:start
Thank you for another
valuable learning experience.

00:34:43.819 --> 00:34:44.587 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ROBERT]
I don't care.

00:34:44.621 --> 00:34:47.023 position:24% line:83% align:start
Request it through
Foreign Affairs.

00:34:47.056 --> 00:34:48.690 position:16% line:89% align:start
We're the victims here.

00:34:48.724 --> 00:34:52.195 position:13% line:83% align:start
Stripping them of military
affiliation isn't nearly enough.

00:34:52.228 --> 00:34:55.965 position:19% line:83% align:start
The government owes me
compensation for this mess.

00:34:58.067 --> 00:35:00.203 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAZ]
That "victim" is bad news.

00:35:00.236 --> 00:35:02.338 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] That's Far East
Trade's representative,

00:35:02.372 --> 00:35:03.339 position:33% line:89% align:start
Robert Lee.

00:35:03.373 --> 00:35:05.408 position:10% line:89% align:start
He's also an infamous fixer.

00:35:05.441 --> 00:35:07.809 position:24% line:83% align:start
Once, the American
government even requested

00:35:07.843 --> 00:35:09.078 position:21% line:89% align:start
that we deport him,

00:35:09.112 --> 00:35:11.713 position:7% line:83% align:start
but not surprisingly, he found
some way to weasel out of it.

00:35:11.747 --> 00:35:13.950 position:30% line:83% align:start
He's got balls
making such a big stink

00:35:13.983 --> 00:35:15.418 position:5% line:89% align:start
when he might still be a target.

00:35:15.451 --> 00:35:17.753 position:27% line:83% align:start
He probably has
a whole host of secrets

00:35:17.786 --> 00:35:19.255 position:7% line:89% align:start
he wants to keep under wraps.

00:35:19.289 --> 00:35:21.324 position:19% line:83% align:start
At any rate, it makes
me wonder who arranged

00:35:21.357 --> 00:35:24.160 position:19% line:83% align:start
the secret talks with
the Prime Minister.

00:35:24.194 --> 00:35:26.795 position:30% line:83% align:start
And who leaked
their location.

00:35:26.829 --> 00:35:27.729 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right?

00:35:27.763 --> 00:35:30.300 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm always open to
a joint investigation.

00:35:30.333 --> 00:35:32.402 position:10% line:89% align:start
Tell the Major that for me.

00:35:32.435 --> 00:35:35.405 position:19% line:89% align:start
[car door clicks open]

00:35:35.438 --> 00:35:38.107 position:27% line:89% align:start
[engine starts]

00:35:50.520 --> 00:35:52.155 position:35% line:83% align:start
[AMAGATA]
Cyberbrain standards are like

00:35:52.188 --> 00:35:54.123 position:27% line:83% align:start
national borders
for corporations.

00:35:54.157 --> 00:35:55.757 position:7% line:89% align:start
Even if those boundaries cause

00:35:55.792 --> 00:35:57.527 position:24% line:83% align:start
technological gaps
between nations,

00:35:57.560 --> 00:35:59.362 position:24% line:83% align:start
that doesn't mean
a country should simply

00:35:59.395 --> 00:36:01.064 position:16% line:89% align:start
relinquish its borders.

00:36:01.097 --> 00:36:04.067 position:10% line:83% align:start
Kurutsu and I were trying to
find a way to the next epoch

00:36:04.100 --> 00:36:06.169 position:27% line:83% align:start
and some people
couldn't handle it.

00:36:06.202 --> 00:36:08.538 position:16% line:83% align:start
Odd hearing that, since
your people have profited

00:36:08.571 --> 00:36:10.840 position:24% line:83% align:start
from a system that
transcends borders,

00:36:10.873 --> 00:36:12.976 position:16% line:89% align:start
Deputy Director Amagata.

00:36:13.009 --> 00:36:14.978 position:13% line:89% align:start
That's no longer my title.

00:36:15.011 --> 00:36:17.046 position:5% line:89% align:start
But Kurutsu said the same thing.

00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:20.149 position:7% line:83% align:start
And I do believe that the day
will come when cyberbrain Nets

00:36:20.183 --> 00:36:21.985 position:10% line:89% align:start
transcend corporate borders.

00:36:22.018 --> 00:36:24.420 position:30% line:83% align:start
It just isn't
that time now.

00:36:24.454 --> 00:36:26.356 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you feel as though
you're in danger,

00:36:26.389 --> 00:36:29.892 position:16% line:83% align:start
we can provide security
and monitoring for you.

00:36:29.926 --> 00:36:32.228 position:16% line:89% align:start
That won't be necessary.

00:36:32.262 --> 00:36:37.033 position:5% line:83% align:start
Your former colleagues will keep
me and my company quite safe.

00:36:43.539 --> 00:36:45.041 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Major.

00:36:45.074 --> 00:36:46.376 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
You've got the info?

00:36:46.409 --> 00:36:47.910 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
No luck with the jamming yet,

00:36:47.944 --> 00:36:50.380 position:7% line:83% align:start
but I did find a data transfer
from Kurutsu.

00:36:50.413 --> 00:36:54.017 position:5% line:83% align:start
It was an outside transmission,
sent one minute after the blast.

00:36:54.050 --> 00:36:55.084 position:21% line:89% align:start
And before you ask,

00:36:55.118 --> 00:36:58.955 position:16% line:83% align:start
it wasn't some testament
sent to the military Net.

00:36:58.988 --> 00:36:59.956 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Give me the address.

00:36:59.989 --> 00:37:01.457 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'll head over there.

00:37:13.903 --> 00:37:15.905 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] So, all the
old members of the 501

00:37:15.938 --> 00:37:18.141 position:27% line:83% align:start
have turned into
corporate employees now?

00:37:18.174 --> 00:37:20.476 position:7% line:89% align:start
Or are you research subjects?

00:37:20.510 --> 00:37:23.112 position:21% line:83% align:start
[IBACHI] Please stay
out of this, Kusanagi.

00:37:23.146 --> 00:37:24.981 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hello, Ibachi.

00:37:25.014 --> 00:37:27.083 position:27% line:83% align:start
Find another job
and walk away.

00:37:27.116 --> 00:37:29.952 position:30% line:83% align:start
We will avenge
Kurutsu on our terms.

00:37:29.986 --> 00:37:31.554 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're nothing but
an outcast now.

00:37:31.588 --> 00:37:34.924 position:5% line:83% align:start
Scrounging around for scraps to
keep that of yours body running.

00:37:34.957 --> 00:37:37.026 position:7% line:89% align:start
I will wreck you if I have to.

00:37:37.060 --> 00:37:39.929 position:10% line:89% align:start
I won't hold back this time.

00:37:50.940 --> 00:37:52.475 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Keep tabs on
everyone at Harimadara

00:37:52.508 --> 00:37:53.976 position:19% line:89% align:start
who came from the 501.

00:37:54.010 --> 00:37:55.546 position:5% line:89% align:start
We might have some obstructions.

00:37:55.579 --> 00:37:56.379 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Roger.

00:37:56.412 --> 00:37:59.550 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm sure they're
hungry for revenge.

00:37:59.583 --> 00:38:00.983 position:16% line:89% align:start
I found a government doc

00:38:01.017 --> 00:38:02.952 position:13% line:83% align:start
referencing developmental
dead ends.

00:38:02.985 --> 00:38:04.220 position:16% line:89% align:start
Twenty or so years back,

00:38:04.253 --> 00:38:06.322 position:21% line:83% align:start
the national policy
caused a real mess,

00:38:06.356 --> 00:38:09.492 position:7% line:83% align:start
so they set up a security plan
for the future.

00:38:09.526 --> 00:38:11.528 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Why would they need that?

00:38:11.562 --> 00:38:14.030 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Evidently a ton
of people went missing.

00:38:14.063 --> 00:38:16.132 position:10% line:83% align:start
Some prosthetics researcher
and his pregnant wife

00:38:16.165 --> 00:38:17.400 position:10% line:89% align:start
are at the top of the list.

00:38:17.433 --> 00:38:21.572 position:5% line:83% align:start
They were last seen at the site
of a chemical weapons explosion.

00:38:24.575 --> 00:38:26.242 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Now it looks
like some organization

00:38:26.275 --> 00:38:29.613 position:16% line:83% align:start
is keeping their bodies
for research.

00:38:29.646 --> 00:38:32.081 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hey! Are you listening?

00:38:34.283 --> 00:38:36.219 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I'll have my AIs
analyze the data.

00:38:36.252 --> 00:38:39.456 position:16% line:83% align:start
Try to find a connection
with our current case.

00:38:48.297 --> 00:38:50.601 position:10% line:83% align:start
[CARETAKER 6A] They tell me
you moved to a new unit.

00:38:53.704 --> 00:38:55.938 position:10% line:83% align:start
[CARETAKER 6A] We see a lot
more non-military companies

00:38:55.972 --> 00:38:57.039 position:19% line:89% align:start
interested these days.

00:38:57.073 --> 00:39:00.109 position:7% line:83% align:start
That leads to a broader range
of jobs, thankfully.

00:39:00.143 --> 00:39:02.278 position:10% line:83% align:start
And they're good investments
for the corporations?

00:39:02.311 --> 00:39:06.349 position:5% line:83% align:start
The point is we can provide our
children with a peaceful future.

00:39:09.152 --> 00:39:11.388 position:24% line:89% align:start
And here they are.

00:39:11.422 --> 00:39:18.729 position:21% line:89% align:start
[CHILDREN laughing]

00:39:18.762 --> 00:39:20.196 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
Hello.

00:39:20.229 --> 00:39:23.500 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's nice to meet you.
My name is Motoko.

00:39:23.534 --> 00:39:25.101 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
I'm Chris.

00:39:25.134 --> 00:39:27.170 position:24% line:83% align:start
You know I used to
live here myself,

00:39:27.203 --> 00:39:29.706 position:7% line:89% align:start
but that was a few years back.

00:39:29.740 --> 00:39:32.041 position:24% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS] Is it nice
to come visit?

00:39:32.074 --> 00:39:33.309 position:35% line:89% align:start
I suppose.

00:39:33.343 --> 00:39:35.579 position:24% line:83% align:start
I need to ask you
about an old friend.

00:39:35.612 --> 00:39:37.548 position:21% line:89% align:start
Her name is Kurutsu.

00:39:37.581 --> 00:39:39.015 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
Of course.

00:39:39.048 --> 00:39:41.050 position:16% line:89% align:start
Everyone here knows her.

00:39:41.083 --> 00:39:45.188 position:7% line:83% align:start
She was building us a future,
until she died.

00:39:45.221 --> 00:39:47.458 position:21% line:83% align:start
May I listen to the
message she left you?

00:39:47.491 --> 00:39:49.025 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
Yes.

00:39:58.602 --> 00:39:59.603 position:35% line:83% align:start
If you're
watching this,

00:39:59.636 --> 00:40:01.438 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid I have
some bad news.

00:40:01.472 --> 00:40:03.407 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm not sure of the
exact circumstances,

00:40:03.440 --> 00:40:05.709 position:24% line:83% align:start
but it seems I've
left this world.

00:40:05.742 --> 00:40:08.378 position:10% line:83% align:start
Check your individual Nets,
there's rights,

00:40:08.412 --> 00:40:12.616 position:7% line:83% align:start
a series of assets, and duties
I've assigned to you.

00:40:12.649 --> 00:40:15.385 position:33% line:83% align:start
Don't worry,
your future is safe.

00:40:15.419 --> 00:40:17.354 position:10% line:89% align:start
Believe in the Third World.

00:40:17.387 --> 00:40:20.257 position:13% line:89% align:start
We'll meet again someday.

00:40:21.258 --> 00:40:24.394 position:13% line:89% align:start
What is "the Third World"?

00:40:24.428 --> 00:40:27.631 position:16% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS] A world of data
without people or things.

00:40:27.664 --> 00:40:29.466 position:27% line:83% align:start
So, even if our
bodies break down

00:40:29.500 --> 00:40:32.769 position:7% line:83% align:start
and we can't swap prosthetics
to stay alive anymore,

00:40:32.803 --> 00:40:35.606 position:27% line:83% align:start
we don't have to
disappear forever.

00:40:35.639 --> 00:40:38.074 position:24% line:83% align:start
Do you believe in
a place like that?

00:40:38.107 --> 00:40:40.477 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's not something
I can know.

00:40:40.511 --> 00:40:42.646 position:13% line:89% align:start
Is this the only message?

00:40:42.679 --> 00:40:44.146 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
Mm.

00:40:45.749 --> 00:40:48.285 position:38% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS]
Can we talk again?

00:40:48.318 --> 00:40:53.423 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO chuckles] Of course.
I'll look forward to it.

00:41:01.798 --> 00:41:02.699 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Oh!

00:41:02.733 --> 00:41:03.634 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Why do we have
to meet in person?

00:41:03.667 --> 00:41:06.570 position:24% line:83% align:start
You telling me my
cyber lobby is bugged?

00:41:06.603 --> 00:41:09.105 position:19% line:83% align:start
No. I just thought we
could have a meal together

00:41:09.138 --> 00:41:11.208 position:27% line:83% align:start
instead of doing
everything by cyberbrain.

00:41:11.241 --> 00:41:11.909 position:30% line:89% align:start
It'd be nice!

00:41:11.942 --> 00:41:13.710 position:33% line:83% align:start
What are you
talking about?

00:41:13.744 --> 00:41:15.612 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] You're the one
who invited this flesh bag

00:41:15.646 --> 00:41:17.447 position:19% line:89% align:start
to the team, remember?

00:41:17.481 --> 00:41:19.483 position:24% line:89% align:start
So don't complain.

00:41:24.588 --> 00:41:26.623 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] You got our rookie
here real scared.

00:41:26.657 --> 00:41:29.326 position:7% line:83% align:start
He said he's afraid you might
be a robot in disguise.

00:41:29.359 --> 00:41:30.761 position:13% line:89% align:start
So he wanted to test you.

00:41:30.794 --> 00:41:32.029 position:16% line:89% align:start
That is not what I said.

00:41:32.061 --> 00:41:34.431 position:7% line:83% align:start
I just thought we could build
some trust if we met for dinner.

00:41:34.464 --> 00:41:36.400 position:10% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] He told me this work
environment is unacceptable.

00:41:36.433 --> 00:41:39.803 position:10% line:83% align:start
No vacation, erratic hours,
unpaid overtime!

00:41:39.836 --> 00:41:42.139 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're making
this stuff up!

00:41:44.408 --> 00:41:45.375 position:27% line:89% align:start
[BATOU chuckles]

00:41:45.409 --> 00:41:47.544 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA gasps]

00:41:52.349 --> 00:41:53.283 position:19% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA clears throat]

00:41:53.317 --> 00:41:54.885 position:13% line:89% align:start
So, the Ministry Faction.

00:41:54.918 --> 00:41:56.820 position:21% line:83% align:start
The eleven guys who
took the hostages,

00:41:56.853 --> 00:42:01.892 position:5% line:83% align:start
Colonel Nada, and seven MIAs all
left the exact same testament.

00:42:01.925 --> 00:42:03.460 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Meaning there's
still a group of them

00:42:03.493 --> 00:42:04.461 position:21% line:89% align:start
out there somewhere,

00:42:04.494 --> 00:42:06.863 position:19% line:83% align:start
lying low and waiting
for a chance to strike.

00:42:06.897 --> 00:42:09.466 position:16% line:83% align:start
Colonel Nada's testament
had an extra line, though,

00:42:09.499 --> 00:42:11.134 position:16% line:89% align:start
and it's a strange one.

00:42:11.168 --> 00:42:14.805 position:10% line:83% align:start
He said he "received a gift
from the Third World."

00:42:14.838 --> 00:42:17.541 position:10% line:83% align:start
Probably just his fancy way
of saying he got the virus

00:42:17.574 --> 00:42:19.209 position:16% line:89% align:start
from the broker, right?

00:42:19.242 --> 00:42:20.811 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
No, it is strange.

00:42:20.844 --> 00:42:22.145 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Huh?

00:42:24.481 --> 00:42:27.484 position:35% line:89% align:start
[slurping]

00:42:27.517 --> 00:42:30.454 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] "Third World"?
Is it like an occult thing?

00:42:30.487 --> 00:42:32.489 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Find out if anyone
at the Ministry of Defense

00:42:32.522 --> 00:42:34.825 position:7% line:83% align:start
or their affiliated companies
have used the phrase.

00:42:34.858 --> 00:42:37.361 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Hire some more people, damn it.

00:42:37.394 --> 00:42:39.329 position:27% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I will,
if I find the right parts.

00:42:39.363 --> 00:42:41.198 position:19% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Treating us
like machines, again?

00:42:41.231 --> 00:42:42.399 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Do you wanna fight about it?

00:42:42.432 --> 00:42:43.867 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Ask the rookie that.

00:42:43.900 --> 00:42:45.268 position:24% line:83% align:start
He said he'd punch
you in the face

00:42:45.302 --> 00:42:47.204 position:5% line:89% align:start
if you called him a part again.

00:42:47.237 --> 00:42:49.740 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] Oh, come on,
does that sound like me?

00:42:49.773 --> 00:42:51.475 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
Got a report for you, Major.

00:42:51.508 --> 00:42:53.543 position:19% line:83% align:start
Judging from the rifle
we confiscated,

00:42:53.577 --> 00:42:55.379 position:13% line:89% align:start
we're dealing with an RMC.

00:42:55.412 --> 00:42:58.749 position:10% line:83% align:start
Meaning there was no sniper,
just a remote-controlled weapon.

00:42:58.782 --> 00:43:00.584 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] So they made
the shot, used the virus

00:43:00.617 --> 00:43:02.619 position:19% line:83% align:start
and remote-controlled
that body all at once?

00:43:02.653 --> 00:43:04.321 position:27% line:83% align:start
They don't just
look like the Major,

00:43:04.354 --> 00:43:06.223 position:10% line:89% align:start
they've got her skills, too!

00:43:06.256 --> 00:43:08.492 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SAITO] Makes me wanna
kill 'em even more.

00:43:08.525 --> 00:43:12.729 position:24% line:83% align:start
Also, I feel like
somebody's been watching me.

00:43:12.763 --> 00:43:15.365 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
Yeah, it's weird.

00:43:15.399 --> 00:43:16.901 position:35% line:89% align:start
So have I.

00:43:21.805 --> 00:43:23.640 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Uh, actually, me too.

00:43:23.674 --> 00:43:25.342 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Ape-Face, maybe?

00:43:25.375 --> 00:43:27.444 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
No, I can't explain it.

00:43:27.477 --> 00:43:30.247 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] I found something
that might be related.

00:43:30.280 --> 00:43:33.383 position:7% line:83% align:start
You're gonna want to see this,
so come to my lobby.

00:43:36.486 --> 00:43:38.321 position:7% line:89% align:start
All right, blow me away, pal.

00:43:38.355 --> 00:43:40.590 position:16% line:83% align:start
I used a forensic search
program to reproduce

00:43:40.624 --> 00:43:43.961 position:7% line:83% align:start
the movements of objects that
got caught in the blast.

00:44:01.344 --> 00:44:03.580 position:21% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] This is pyro
reverse measurement--

00:44:03.613 --> 00:44:06.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
it's like replaying
the explosion backwards.

00:44:06.516 --> 00:44:08.251 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Not bad!

00:44:23.700 --> 00:44:25.937 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] The bomb case used
fingerprint recognition,

00:44:25.970 --> 00:44:28.773 position:24% line:83% align:start
so only the PM or
his aides could open it.

00:44:34.578 --> 00:44:35.880 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
A surveillance camera?

00:44:35.913 --> 00:44:36.881 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
It's military,

00:44:36.914 --> 00:44:38.816 position:19% line:83% align:start
but it's got a limited
range of transmission.

00:44:38.850 --> 00:44:41.418 position:27% line:83% align:start
I tested it with
some white noise.

00:44:41.451 --> 00:44:43.821 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] It's only got
a cheap AI encryption, too.

00:44:43.855 --> 00:44:47.725 position:13% line:83% align:start
Here, I'll connect to our
peeping tom's Net now.

00:44:47.759 --> 00:44:50.560 position:24% line:89% align:start
[OBSERVER A gasps]

00:44:50.594 --> 00:44:52.295 position:24% line:89% align:start
[OBSERVER B gasps]

00:44:52.329 --> 00:44:54.331 position:21% line:89% align:start
[OBSERVER 6A yelps]

00:44:54.364 --> 00:44:56.000 position:7% line:89% align:start
Give me your name and outfit!

00:44:56.033 --> 00:44:57.001 position:30% line:89% align:start
And just FYI,

00:44:57.034 --> 00:45:00.270 position:19% line:83% align:start
my sniper's itching to
kill someone right now.

00:45:07.879 --> 00:45:09.479 position:33% line:83% align:start
[OBSERVER C]
Huh?!

00:45:09.513 --> 00:45:11.381 position:21% line:89% align:start
[OBSERVER C grunts]

00:45:11.414 --> 00:45:13.350 position:19% line:83% align:start
[OBSERVER D] I'm with
the Treaty Review Department,

00:45:13.383 --> 00:45:15.920 position:16% line:89% align:start
Section D! Contact them!

00:45:15.953 --> 00:45:18.321 position:27% line:83% align:start
He's working...
for foreign affairs.

00:45:18.355 --> 00:45:20.792 position:21% line:89% align:start
[OBSERVER E choking]

00:45:20.825 --> 00:45:24.061 position:10% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] These clowns were in
on the PM's secret talks?

00:45:33.137 --> 00:45:34.639 position:16% line:83% align:start
[OBSERVER C, OBSERVER D
grunting]

00:45:34.672 --> 00:45:37.675 position:10% line:89% align:start
[SECURITY MEN, AKIYAMA gasp]

00:45:40.410 --> 00:45:42.947 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm Akiyama. We're from
the Treaty Review Department.

00:45:42.980 --> 00:45:45.883 position:30% line:83% align:start
I want to keep
this brief, okay?

00:45:45.917 --> 00:45:48.619 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA] We captured her
on camera about a month ago.

00:45:48.653 --> 00:45:50.688 position:30% line:83% align:start
Brainwashing,
Ghost infiltration,

00:45:50.721 --> 00:45:52.790 position:13% line:89% align:start
false memory implantation.

00:45:52.824 --> 00:45:54.992 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Fire Starter virus
does it all.

00:45:55.026 --> 00:45:56.894 position:19% line:83% align:start
And this is the maniac
that sells it.

00:45:56.928 --> 00:46:00.463 position:5% line:83% align:start
She actually uses "Fire Starter"
as her handle, too.

00:46:00.497 --> 00:46:01.999 position:24% line:83% align:start
You approached her
to get the virus,

00:46:02.033 --> 00:46:03.701 position:7% line:89% align:start
and fell right into her trap.

00:46:03.734 --> 00:46:06.604 position:7% line:83% align:start
And then, because we happen to
look alike, you track me?

00:46:06.637 --> 00:46:08.039 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're such a fool.

00:46:08.072 --> 00:46:09.874 position:24% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA] You're a
super-wizard-class hacker,

00:46:09.907 --> 00:46:13.778 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'd be an ever bigger fool
if I were to ignore you.

00:46:15.713 --> 00:46:17.748 position:35% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA]
Mm.

00:46:17.782 --> 00:46:20.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
It was two officers
that she manipulated.

00:46:20.517 --> 00:46:21.152 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
"Officers?"

00:46:21.185 --> 00:46:22.286 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's a position--

00:46:22.320 --> 00:46:24.789 position:16% line:83% align:start
someone who helps enact
the Prime Minister's policies.

00:46:24.822 --> 00:46:27.091 position:27% line:83% align:start
One of them was
Colonel Haruyoshi Nada.

00:46:27.124 --> 00:46:29.527 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] The guy who went
missing before the incident.

00:46:29.560 --> 00:46:31.796 position:16% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA] His job was to
isolate the radical elements

00:46:31.829 --> 00:46:33.564 position:10% line:89% align:start
within the Ministry Faction.

00:46:33.598 --> 00:46:36.701 position:10% line:83% align:start
Not the person you'd expect
to launch a terrorist attack.

00:46:36.734 --> 00:46:40.104 position:5% line:83% align:start
It was like he had a personality
transplant or something.

00:46:40.137 --> 00:46:42.506 position:30% line:83% align:start
Then he might
have been infected.

00:46:42.540 --> 00:46:45.009 position:7% line:83% align:start
I doubt the broker would take
things that far, though.

00:46:45.042 --> 00:46:48.779 position:5% line:83% align:start
Some enemies of the PM must have
bought the virus at an auction.

00:46:48.813 --> 00:46:49.981 position:35% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA]
Well, when I get their names,

00:46:50.014 --> 00:46:53.184 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll take them and
the broker down.

00:46:53.217 --> 00:46:54.952 position:7% line:89% align:start
So who was the other officer?

00:46:54.986 --> 00:47:02.994 position:7% line:83% align:start
[AKIYAMA sighs] Yoko Kitahara,
Vice-Minister of Defense.

00:47:06.163 --> 00:47:08.599 position:10% line:89% align:start
What is the meaning of this?

00:47:11.869 --> 00:47:13.204 position:33% line:89% align:start
Don't move!

00:47:13.237 --> 00:47:15.106 position:21% line:83% align:start
There is a protocol
to follow, here!

00:47:15.139 --> 00:47:17.642 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're under arrest for
unlawful investigation!

00:47:17.675 --> 00:47:19.911 position:24% line:89% align:start
Would you stop it?

00:47:22.613 --> 00:47:26.450 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry. I had no idea.

00:47:26.484 --> 00:47:28.920 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Then let's hear your story.

00:47:32.089 --> 00:47:33.791 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
She was infected by Nada,

00:47:33.824 --> 00:47:36.527 position:19% line:83% align:start
and made to antagonize
the Ministry faction.

00:47:36.560 --> 00:47:39.864 position:7% line:83% align:start
Namely, she manipulated public
opinion to favor their downgrade

00:47:39.897 --> 00:47:41.933 position:21% line:83% align:start
and laid off several
thousand troops.

00:47:41.966 --> 00:47:44.535 position:21% line:83% align:start
Was she involved in
the assassination?

00:47:44.568 --> 00:47:46.804 position:30% line:83% align:start
No, not as far
as we can tell.

00:47:46.837 --> 00:47:48.606 position:24% line:83% align:start
This was quite an
elaborate scheme--

00:47:48.639 --> 00:47:50.508 position:30% line:83% align:start
manipulating a
foreign affairs squad

00:47:50.541 --> 00:47:52.877 position:10% line:83% align:start
and the Ministry of Defense
from the inside.

00:47:52.910 --> 00:47:55.146 position:27% line:83% align:start
The virus itself
hasn't been found yet.

00:47:55.179 --> 00:47:57.682 position:16% line:83% align:start
Are you sure this woman
isn't making fools of us?

00:47:57.715 --> 00:48:00.584 position:16% line:83% align:start
Any idiot could tell I'm
a victim in this mess, too.

00:48:00.618 --> 00:48:02.787 position:5% line:89% align:start
Why don't we all point fingers?

00:48:02.820 --> 00:48:04.922 position:21% line:83% align:start
Obviously, somebody
manipulated things

00:48:04.956 --> 00:48:06.257 position:21% line:83% align:start
to make it look like
it was my setup.

00:48:06.290 --> 00:48:07.024 position:35% line:89% align:start
Excuse me?

00:48:07.058 --> 00:48:09.560 position:35% line:83% align:start
Who is he?
He's not Section 9.

00:48:09.593 --> 00:48:12.563 position:19% line:83% align:start
The name is Kuwahara,
he's an intelligence officer.

00:48:12.596 --> 00:48:15.032 position:13% line:83% align:start
The head of their strategy
office, to be precise.

00:48:15.066 --> 00:48:15.933 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KUWAHARA]
Aramaki!

00:48:15.967 --> 00:48:16.801 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
I see.

00:48:16.834 --> 00:48:18.502 position:30% line:83% align:start
So it was the
intelligence division

00:48:18.536 --> 00:48:21.539 position:16% line:83% align:start
that outbid the treaties
bureau for the virus?

00:48:21.572 --> 00:48:23.207 position:10% line:89% align:start
The virus wasn't the point.

00:48:23.240 --> 00:48:25.277 position:24% line:83% align:start
I can't speak for
the treaties bureau,

00:48:25.310 --> 00:48:28.679 position:5% line:83% align:start
but our purchase was supposed to
be a ruse to capture the broker.

00:48:28.713 --> 00:48:31.248 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll just pretend
I believe that.

00:48:31.283 --> 00:48:33.551 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] If we have any
hope to accomplish this,

00:48:33.584 --> 00:48:34.952 position:21% line:83% align:start
we're going to have
to work together.

00:48:34.986 --> 00:48:40.591 position:24% line:83% align:start
Would it kill you
to cooperate, Major?

00:48:40.624 --> 00:48:42.693 position:16% line:83% align:start
When you have to lock up
witnesses and victims

00:48:42.727 --> 00:48:43.995 position:13% line:89% align:start
just to protect yourself,

00:48:44.028 --> 00:48:45.596 position:27% line:83% align:start
you're no better
than the criminals.

00:48:45.629 --> 00:48:48.065 position:13% line:83% align:start
Bold words from the leader
of a glorified gang!

00:48:48.099 --> 00:48:49.301 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
If you want to help so bad,

00:48:49.334 --> 00:48:50.868 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll call you when
I've caught her.

00:48:50.901 --> 00:48:53.971 position:24% line:83% align:start
Then you can come
clean up the mess for me.

00:48:54.005 --> 00:48:55.806 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KUWAHARA growls]

00:49:03.215 --> 00:49:05.649 position:16% line:83% align:start
They could come looking
for me very soon--

00:49:05.683 --> 00:49:08.552 position:19% line:83% align:start
They've already traced
things back to Kitahara.

00:49:08.586 --> 00:49:10.222 position:27% line:83% align:start
They're turning
into a real nuisance.

00:49:10.255 --> 00:49:11.922 position:19% line:83% align:start
Can you take them over
with your virus?

00:49:11.956 --> 00:49:13.291 position:30% line:83% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO]
No need to panic.

00:49:13.325 --> 00:49:15.260 position:21% line:83% align:start
Intelligence and the
Treaty Review Department

00:49:15.293 --> 00:49:16.761 position:16% line:89% align:start
are both under my thumb.

00:49:16.794 --> 00:49:19.130 position:13% line:83% align:start
And truth is the greatest
tragedy of all,

00:49:19.164 --> 00:49:20.664 position:24% line:89% align:start
the greatest trap.

00:49:20.698 --> 00:49:22.099 position:19% line:89% align:start
Patriotism is fickle.

00:49:22.133 --> 00:49:24.668 position:21% line:83% align:start
We can't rely on it
to protect us forever.

00:49:24.702 --> 00:49:25.903 position:33% line:83% align:start
If we don't
take care of them,

00:49:25.936 --> 00:49:28.240 position:19% line:83% align:start
they'll come knocking
on our doors in no time.

00:49:28.273 --> 00:49:31.842 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you can't do it yourself,
then it'll cost you.

00:49:51.929 --> 00:49:53.664 position:30% line:89% align:start
Well, Motoko.

00:49:53.697 --> 00:49:57.335 position:16% line:83% align:start
Shall I steal your name
along with your face?

00:50:00.771 --> 00:50:03.108 position:5% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] This is the second time
I've heard of a secret directive

00:50:03.141 --> 00:50:05.643 position:27% line:83% align:start
issued by the PM
after his death.

00:50:05.676 --> 00:50:08.213 position:5% line:83% align:start
Vice Minister Kitahara said she
couldn't remember the details,

00:50:08.246 --> 00:50:10.881 position:10% line:83% align:start
but if she thinks this ghost
ship off the coast of Niihama

00:50:10.915 --> 00:50:11.849 position:7% line:89% align:start
might have some significance,

00:50:11.882 --> 00:50:14.852 position:16% line:83% align:start
then it's the best lead
we've got right now.

00:50:14.885 --> 00:50:16.188 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
If this is Nada's hideout,

00:50:16.221 --> 00:50:19.023 position:21% line:83% align:start
then why aren't the
intelligence guys making a move?

00:50:19.057 --> 00:50:21.692 position:21% line:83% align:start
The treaties bureau
says he's infected, right?

00:50:21.725 --> 00:50:23.828 position:7% line:89% align:start
Then you know what that means.

00:50:23.861 --> 00:50:27.399 position:13% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] Odds are ten to one
that this is a trap.

00:50:27.432 --> 00:50:29.334 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] It's probably
somewhere in this cluster

00:50:29.367 --> 00:50:31.336 position:21% line:89% align:start
of undersea cables.

00:50:31.369 --> 00:50:33.704 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm thinking it's a spy vessel.

00:50:33.737 --> 00:50:35.773 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] If intelligence
hadn't stolen Kitahara from us,

00:50:35.806 --> 00:50:38.276 position:5% line:83% align:start
we'd probably have better info.
What's your call?

00:50:38.310 --> 00:50:41.113 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] We'll figure out the
rest when we storm the ship.

00:50:43.014 --> 00:50:46.017 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Hmph. Any excuse
to blow stuff up.

00:50:46.051 --> 00:50:49.221 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] You knew what
you were getting into.

00:50:49.254 --> 00:50:51.056 position:7% line:89% align:start
The truth isn't served to us.

00:50:51.089 --> 00:50:52.823 position:21% line:89% align:start
We have to seize it.

00:50:52.857 --> 00:50:55.327 position:27% line:83% align:start
So can you deal
with that, or not?

00:50:55.360 --> 00:50:57.962 position:24% line:83% align:start
You'll have to let
your Ghost decide.

00:51:46.044 --> 00:51:47.979 position:24% line:83% align:start
We're fighting for
the future this time.

00:51:48.013 --> 00:51:50.315 position:27% line:83% align:start
Not for another
bloody battlefield, right?

00:51:50.348 --> 00:51:53.351 position:16% line:83% align:start
Not for some cramped up
little corner to die in.

00:51:53.385 --> 00:51:56.254 position:27% line:83% align:start
But for a place
we can call home.

00:51:59.224 --> 00:52:02.327 position:16% line:83% align:start
If nothing else, I think
I can work us into a position

00:52:02.360 --> 00:52:05.297 position:21% line:83% align:start
that's better suited
to our talents.

00:52:15.473 --> 00:52:16.942 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Stand by for now.

00:52:16.975 --> 00:52:19.177 position:24% line:83% align:start
We don't know what
we're up against.

00:52:19.211 --> 00:52:22.247 position:21% line:83% align:start
"An offensive unit,
free of the system."

00:52:22.280 --> 00:52:25.016 position:19% line:83% align:start
It sounds like nothing
more than a pipe dream.

00:52:25.050 --> 00:52:27.953 position:16% line:83% align:start
Their skills would have
to be irreplaceable,

00:52:27.986 --> 00:52:30.455 position:19% line:89% align:start
but perhaps they are.

00:52:36.228 --> 00:52:38.363 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
No sign of anyone onboard.

00:52:56.881 --> 00:52:58.283 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
Incoming!

00:53:01.553 --> 00:53:03.255 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

00:53:03.288 --> 00:53:05.757 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Wow, tanks already, huh?

00:53:07.025 --> 00:53:09.094 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] I knew I shoulda
stayed at home today.

00:53:09.127 --> 00:53:10.462 position:41% line:89% align:start
Saito!

00:53:11.997 --> 00:53:13.965 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
I can't pick them up!

00:53:16.101 --> 00:53:22.307 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Damn. That's type
2902 thermo-optical camouflage.

00:53:22.340 --> 00:53:24.142 position:16% line:89% align:start
Kyo-Re's newest release!

00:53:24.175 --> 00:53:25.343 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
How much capital have they got

00:53:25.377 --> 00:53:28.546 position:5% line:83% align:start
if they can hook up their troops
and their tanks with that?

00:53:31.583 --> 00:53:34.019 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
I'm taking the ship. Cover me!

00:53:35.520 --> 00:53:38.423 position:30% line:89% align:start
How, exactly?!

00:53:38.456 --> 00:53:41.226 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] I'll show you
how it's done, rookie.

00:53:47.633 --> 00:53:49.167 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER B grunts]

00:53:55.373 --> 00:53:56.274 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
Move!

00:53:56.308 --> 00:53:57.842 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

00:54:24.302 --> 00:54:24.836 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER C gasps]

00:54:24.869 --> 00:54:31.509 position:16% line:89% align:start
[LOGICOMA ALL screaming]

00:54:35.347 --> 00:54:37.349 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER C groans]

00:54:53.131 --> 00:54:54.899 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU grunts]

00:54:54.933 --> 00:54:55.967 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER D grunts]

00:54:56.000 --> 00:54:58.002 position:19% line:89% align:start
I've got this one! Go!

00:55:18.189 --> 00:55:20.425 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I've reached the
intermediate security server.

00:55:20.459 --> 00:55:23.294 position:30% line:83% align:start
I can see the
barrier's gate array.

00:55:25.430 --> 00:55:27.298 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Looks a lot like
the tactical defense kind

00:55:27.332 --> 00:55:29.200 position:16% line:89% align:start
army intelligence uses.

00:55:29.234 --> 00:55:31.570 position:24% line:83% align:start
Lots of entrances,
but only one exit.

00:55:31.604 --> 00:55:34.038 position:24% line:89% align:start
This'll be a pain.

00:55:34.072 --> 00:55:35.674 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Opening a tunnel.

00:55:35.708 --> 00:55:38.009 position:21% line:83% align:start
Damn, they filled it
with null data.

00:55:38.042 --> 00:55:39.512 position:10% line:89% align:start
This is gonna take a second.

00:55:39.545 --> 00:55:41.212 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
I've seen this method before.

00:55:41.246 --> 00:55:43.314 position:16% line:83% align:start
The real data's probably
right behind the nulls.

00:55:43.348 --> 00:55:44.983 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
I'll keep looking.

00:55:45.016 --> 00:55:47.986 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] Don't bother.
I'll force it open.

00:55:49.588 --> 00:55:51.322 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO gasps]

00:55:53.692 --> 00:55:57.730 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

00:55:57.763 --> 00:56:00.064 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Your protection
from the broadcast shorted out!

00:56:00.098 --> 00:56:01.367 position:19% line:89% align:start
Close the connection!

00:56:01.400 --> 00:56:03.502 position:35% line:89% align:start
Too late!

00:56:03.536 --> 00:56:05.069 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:56:09.642 --> 00:56:11.644 position:21% line:89% align:start
[LOGICOMA grunting]

00:56:19.250 --> 00:56:21.387 position:24% line:89% align:start
What the--? Aaah!

00:56:23.221 --> 00:56:26.425 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Jeez, how many
hidden servers do you got?

00:56:26.459 --> 00:56:28.193 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
You don't storm a place unarmed.

00:56:28.226 --> 00:56:32.096 position:21% line:83% align:start
I've taken control.
The info-- [gasps]

00:56:32.130 --> 00:56:33.466 position:30% line:89% align:start
What is this?

00:56:36.402 --> 00:56:39.338 position:33% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER E]
Signals 2, 6, and 7 lost.

00:56:39.371 --> 00:56:41.474 position:19% line:83% align:start
Number and positioning
of enemy troops unknown.

00:56:41.507 --> 00:56:44.410 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER F] Damn it! They've
taken our fire-control room!

00:56:47.212 --> 00:56:48.547 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIERS gasping]

00:56:52.284 --> 00:56:53.151 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER O groans]

00:56:53.184 --> 00:56:53.652 position:33% line:83% align:start
[SOLDIER G]
Ah!

00:56:53.686 --> 00:56:55.354 position:27% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER groans]

00:56:55.387 --> 00:56:56.722 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
What?!

00:56:56.755 --> 00:57:00.759 position:21% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIERS groaning]

00:57:06.632 --> 00:57:08.467 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Okay, I got him.

00:57:13.204 --> 00:57:15.206 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
We're done here, too.

00:57:16.375 --> 00:57:17.710 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
Hm?

00:57:20.412 --> 00:57:22.180 position:27% line:83% align:start
--Hit the deck!
--[TOGUSA gasps]

00:57:26.652 --> 00:57:29.522 position:5% line:83% align:start
--[BATOU] Another stinkin' tank!
--[LOGICOMA 6A] Mr. Batou!

00:57:35.628 --> 00:57:37.061 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
And stop!

00:57:37.095 --> 00:57:39.097 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Can we get you
a cockpit already?!

00:57:39.130 --> 00:57:42.434 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Your request is being processed!

00:57:42.468 --> 00:57:44.470 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Military restructuring?

00:57:44.503 --> 00:57:48.139 position:33% line:83% align:start
Why my team?
Who the hell did this?

00:57:48.173 --> 00:57:49.742 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:57:52.411 --> 00:57:54.713 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
So that's how it is.

00:57:54.747 --> 00:57:58.082 position:30% line:89% align:start
[alarms sound]

00:57:58.116 --> 00:58:01.085 position:24% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Get the
hell out of there, Major!

00:58:01.119 --> 00:58:03.289 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Major! What's your status?!

00:58:10.396 --> 00:58:12.498 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Would somebody
tell me what's going on?!

00:58:12.531 --> 00:58:14.500 position:19% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Pretty sure
we took over the ship.

00:58:14.533 --> 00:58:15.834 position:27% line:83% align:start
Someone must be
remote-controlling

00:58:15.868 --> 00:58:17.836 position:13% line:89% align:start
these things from nearby.

00:58:19.471 --> 00:58:23.275 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Saito! Find them and kill them!

00:58:23.309 --> 00:58:24.510 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
I need more intel!

00:58:24.543 --> 00:58:25.844 position:30% line:89% align:start
[SAITO gasps]

00:58:28.547 --> 00:58:30.416 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
That bitch!

00:58:32.851 --> 00:58:34.386 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wow, nice shot!

00:58:34.420 --> 00:58:36.755 position:16% line:83% align:start
You can come work for me
after we kill your boss!

00:58:44.296 --> 00:58:47.099 position:27% line:83% align:start
[SAITO] Dammit!
She's getting away again!

00:58:55.674 --> 00:58:57.576 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] Wait, why aren't
they shooting at us?

00:58:57.610 --> 00:59:01.146 position:21% line:83% align:start
Isn't their goal to
take back the ship?

00:59:01.180 --> 00:59:02.514 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Everyone all right?

00:59:02.548 --> 00:59:03.449 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Yeah, and you?

00:59:03.482 --> 00:59:05.517 position:19% line:83% align:start
--[SAITO, BATOU gasp]
--[PAZ] Whoa, huh?

00:59:05.551 --> 00:59:06.518 position:21% line:89% align:start
She forced us here.

00:59:06.552 --> 00:59:09.488 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah, and she didn't use
Ghost infiltration keys.

00:59:09.521 --> 00:59:11.857 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] There's no time,
so I'll make this brief.

00:59:11.890 --> 00:59:15.461 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm restarting the investigation
with a new hypothesis.

00:59:15.494 --> 00:59:18.764 position:13% line:83% align:start
The rest of you don't need
to bear the risk this time.

00:59:18.797 --> 00:59:19.865 position:35% line:89% align:start
But Major?

00:59:19.898 --> 00:59:22.401 position:33% line:83% align:start
It's data--
that's not really her.

00:59:22.434 --> 00:59:25.537 position:10% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] The squad has been
officially disbanded.

00:59:25.571 --> 00:59:26.639 position:35% line:83% align:start
--But why?
--[ISHIKAWA, BORMA gasp]

00:59:26.672 --> 00:59:28.540 position:21% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] I'll leave
recommendation letters for you

00:59:28.574 --> 00:59:29.575 position:21% line:89% align:start
with Chief Aramaki.

00:59:29.608 --> 00:59:32.745 position:10% line:83% align:start
Of course, you can transfer
wherever you want.

00:59:32.778 --> 00:59:35.314 position:19% line:83% align:start
You're the best parts
in the business.

00:59:35.347 --> 00:59:38.617 position:19% line:83% align:start
When you're together,
you make the perfect machine.

00:59:38.651 --> 00:59:41.286 position:10% line:83% align:start
You'll accomplish more than
I could ever dream of.

00:59:41.320 --> 00:59:44.958 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU gasps]

00:59:44.991 --> 00:59:46.492 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
That's all.

00:59:46.525 --> 00:59:48.427 position:24% line:89% align:start
Follow your Ghost.

00:59:49.929 --> 00:59:50.796 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:59:50.829 --> 00:59:52.531 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Her lobby's been shut down.

00:59:52.564 --> 00:59:55.567 position:19% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] What the hell?
Did she purge herself?

00:59:55.601 --> 00:59:58.404 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAZ]
She might've just cut us off.

00:59:58.437 --> 01:00:00.606 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
It's messed up either way.

01:00:00.639 --> 01:00:04.510 position:19% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA gasps, grunts]

01:00:06.812 --> 01:00:10.816 position:10% line:83% align:start
[BATOU grunts] My ghost lock
won't work on this guy!

01:00:19.525 --> 01:00:20.860 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Huh?!

01:00:22.494 --> 01:00:25.165 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Must be a
remote-controlled body.

01:00:48.287 --> 01:00:50.990 position:13% line:83% align:start
[KITAHARA] Were they able
to capture Colonel Nada?

01:00:52.591 --> 01:00:53.860 position:16% line:83% align:start
[KITAHARA] You're still
upset that the hearing

01:00:53.893 --> 01:00:56.562 position:19% line:83% align:start
has been put on hold,
aren't you?

01:00:56.595 --> 01:00:57.730 position:16% line:89% align:start
Well, don't look at me!

01:00:57.763 --> 01:01:00.432 position:24% line:83% align:start
I don't know what
the truth is anymore.

01:01:00.466 --> 01:01:02.802 position:21% line:89% align:start
Who said I'm upset?

01:01:02.836 --> 01:01:04.369 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:01:44.343 --> 01:01:45.912 position:30% line:83% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO]
I'm borrowing another car.

01:01:45.945 --> 01:01:48.447 position:16% line:83% align:start
Send the repair bill to
the Ministry of Commerce

01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:51.517 position:7% line:89% align:start
or the Far East trade embassy.

01:01:51.550 --> 01:01:53.720 position:24% line:83% align:start
Tell me something,
"Fire-Starter,"

01:01:53.753 --> 01:01:56.756 position:7% line:83% align:start
Was that the code name for the
virus during its development?

01:01:56.790 --> 01:01:59.358 position:27% line:83% align:start
Or was it simply
your name all along?

01:01:59.391 --> 01:02:02.695 position:19% line:83% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO] Is there
a difference, really?

01:02:02.729 --> 01:02:05.430 position:7% line:83% align:start
[KUWAHARA] I abandoned the spy
vessel, just like you asked.

01:02:05.464 --> 01:02:08.001 position:7% line:89% align:start
What more do you want from me?

01:02:08.034 --> 01:02:09.936 position:19% line:83% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO] For one,
I don't know if Kusanagi

01:02:09.969 --> 01:02:11.537 position:19% line:89% align:start
is still alive or not.

01:02:11.570 --> 01:02:14.707 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why don't you try
searching your Net for her?

01:02:14.741 --> 01:02:16.743 position:16% line:89% align:start
Thanks for cooperating.

01:02:16.776 --> 01:02:19.078 position:21% line:83% align:start
We wouldn't want the
biggest scandal since the war

01:02:19.112 --> 01:02:21.748 position:10% line:89% align:start
to go public, now would we?

01:02:35.561 --> 01:02:37.864 position:5% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] Vice-Minister Kitahara
was assassinated,

01:02:37.897 --> 01:02:40.499 position:13% line:83% align:start
and Colonel Nada's status
is still unknown.

01:02:40.532 --> 01:02:42.869 position:19% line:83% align:start
That makes your claims
difficult to corroborate,

01:02:42.902 --> 01:02:46.505 position:10% line:83% align:start
especially since you've lost
your investigative privileges.

01:02:46.538 --> 01:02:48.041 position:5% line:89% align:start
Still, you can stay on the case

01:02:48.074 --> 01:02:50.777 position:30% line:83% align:start
if you become
members of Section 9.

01:02:50.810 --> 01:02:54.446 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, that's not gonna happen.

01:02:54.479 --> 01:02:54.981 position:30% line:89% align:start
So long, pal.

01:02:55.014 --> 01:02:56.649 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Hey, wait!

01:02:56.683 --> 01:02:58.751 position:21% line:83% align:start
Are you really gonna
let it end like this?

01:03:02.121 --> 01:03:04.891 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

01:03:04.924 --> 01:03:08.161 position:19% line:83% align:start
So where do you think
we should start?

01:03:08.194 --> 01:03:09.996 position:21% line:83% align:start
If the ship doesn't
give us anything,

01:03:10.029 --> 01:03:11.998 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'd look into anybody
involved in the case

01:03:12.031 --> 01:03:13.800 position:16% line:89% align:start
who refuses to testify.

01:03:13.833 --> 01:03:16.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] Like Robert Lee?
The Far East trade rep?

01:03:16.936 --> 01:03:18.838 position:5% line:89% align:start
That one's a tough nut to crack.

01:03:18.872 --> 01:03:20.807 position:13% line:89% align:start
Try using Section 9's Net.

01:03:20.840 --> 01:03:22.575 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Yes, sir!

01:03:27.013 --> 01:03:29.949 position:13% line:83% align:start
The seeds that you planted
are bearing fruit, Major.

01:03:29.983 --> 01:03:32.085 position:7% line:89% align:start
I won't let them be cut down.

01:03:32.118 --> 01:03:34.654 position:38% line:89% align:start
I swear.

01:03:34.687 --> 01:03:40.760 position:30% line:89% align:start
[piano plays]

01:03:40.793 --> 01:03:42.762 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
I caught some strange intel.

01:03:42.795 --> 01:03:45.999 position:7% line:83% align:start
While back, a husband and wife
team of prosthetics developers

01:03:46.032 --> 01:03:48.735 position:7% line:83% align:start
went missing during a project
to avoid dead-ending.

01:03:48.768 --> 01:03:50.536 position:27% line:83% align:start
Did some digging
and it turns out,

01:03:50.570 --> 01:03:52.906 position:27% line:83% align:start
their bodies are
being kept by Unit 501

01:03:52.939 --> 01:03:55.975 position:16% line:89% align:start
for "research purposes."

01:03:56.009 --> 01:03:59.112 position:5% line:83% align:start
You better not tell me the wife
was about to have a damn baby.

01:03:59.145 --> 01:04:01.514 position:24% line:83% align:start
Is there something
I'm missing here?

01:04:03.016 --> 01:04:06.886 position:10% line:83% align:start
Think of someone who's been
a full cyborg since birth.

01:04:06.920 --> 01:04:09.155 position:10% line:89% align:start
They're the Major's parents?

01:04:09.188 --> 01:04:10.723 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
I wish I could tell you.

01:04:10.757 --> 01:04:14.928 position:5% line:83% align:start
The bodies are so contaminated,
they can't even be ID'd.

01:04:16.696 --> 01:04:19.032 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] The Major was born
without a body of her own

01:04:19.065 --> 01:04:21.601 position:7% line:89% align:start
and raised as army equipment.

01:04:21.634 --> 01:04:24.037 position:21% line:83% align:start
She really did have
nothing to lose.

01:04:24.070 --> 01:04:25.705 position:5% line:89% align:start
She was someone else's property

01:04:25.738 --> 01:04:29.042 position:21% line:83% align:start
without any hope of
achieving freedom.

01:04:29.075 --> 01:04:31.010 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BORMA] That's why
she was working so hard

01:04:31.044 --> 01:04:34.514 position:5% line:89% align:start
to go independent after the war.

01:04:34.547 --> 01:04:36.482 position:21% line:83% align:start
So your take is that
she's acting on her own

01:04:36.516 --> 01:04:39.118 position:27% line:83% align:start
because of these
parents of hers?

01:04:39.152 --> 01:04:40.853 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
She's not that sentimental.

01:04:40.887 --> 01:04:43.022 position:13% line:83% align:start
They're probably secondary
to some bigger fish

01:04:43.056 --> 01:04:44.590 position:24% line:89% align:start
she wants to fry.

01:04:44.624 --> 01:04:46.225 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's not like I have proof,

01:04:46.259 --> 01:04:49.629 position:13% line:83% align:start
but it feels like she saw
something real bad on that ship.

01:04:49.662 --> 01:04:51.764 position:19% line:83% align:start
Bad enough for her to
purge every one of us

01:04:51.798 --> 01:04:53.800 position:13% line:89% align:start
without a second thought.

01:04:53.833 --> 01:04:56.035 position:21% line:83% align:start
If you're suggesting
she did that to protect us,

01:04:56.069 --> 01:04:57.103 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm not buying it.

01:04:57.136 --> 01:05:00.106 position:19% line:83% align:start
This is the woman who
calls us "parts" you know!

01:05:00.139 --> 01:05:01.908 position:27% line:83% align:start
She can call us
whatever she wants,

01:05:01.941 --> 01:05:03.977 position:21% line:83% align:start
all that matters is
how she treats us.

01:05:04.010 --> 01:05:07.680 position:16% line:83% align:start
I shouldn't kid myself.
Full cyborgs are parts, really.

01:05:07.714 --> 01:05:10.284 position:13% line:83% align:start
Gotta join an organization
to do maintenance for you,

01:05:10.317 --> 01:05:14.020 position:19% line:83% align:start
or you fall apart long
before you're dead.

01:05:25.798 --> 01:05:28.201 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BORMA]
Where are you going?

01:05:28.235 --> 01:05:32.138 position:7% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] I'm not the kinda guy
who can just "follow his Ghost."

01:05:32.171 --> 01:05:36.075 position:7% line:83% align:start
If I can't see it with my own
eyes, then it ain't real.

01:05:38.845 --> 01:05:43.016 position:7% line:83% align:start
A giant ship, seven soldiers,
and two of those tanks.

01:05:43.049 --> 01:05:46.719 position:19% line:83% align:start
That sure was one hell
of an expensive trap.

01:06:14.814 --> 01:06:17.817 position:24% line:83% align:start
What the hell were
they all looking at?

01:06:31.631 --> 01:06:34.801 position:7% line:89% align:start
I thought maybe we could talk.

01:06:39.739 --> 01:06:41.175 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
I know it's sudden.

01:06:41.208 --> 01:06:42.708 position:19% line:89% align:start
Thanks for coming out.

01:06:42.742 --> 01:06:45.212 position:16% line:83% align:start
So you want to work for
intelligence again, huh?

01:06:45.245 --> 01:06:47.980 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you can give me some
good intel on Major Kusanagi,

01:06:48.014 --> 01:06:50.084 position:21% line:89% align:start
I might consider it.

01:06:51.717 --> 01:06:54.887 position:19% line:83% align:start
You're the one who's
doing the talking.

01:06:57.257 --> 01:07:00.827 position:21% line:83% align:start
My role here, was to
serve as a relay point.

01:07:00.860 --> 01:07:02.229 position:30% line:89% align:start
I was certain.

01:07:02.262 --> 01:07:04.164 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
You're Koichi Sawada?

01:07:04.198 --> 01:07:06.933 position:19% line:83% align:start
Formerly of the Army's
armored division?

01:07:06.966 --> 01:07:09.136 position:16% line:83% align:start
'Cause that name matches
one of the Ministry loyalists

01:07:09.169 --> 01:07:11.904 position:30% line:83% align:start
who died on a
spy ship yesterday.

01:07:11.938 --> 01:07:14.208 position:30% line:89% align:start
I don't know.

01:07:17.677 --> 01:07:20.314 position:7% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] You've been implanted
with false memories,

01:07:20.347 --> 01:07:22.982 position:16% line:89% align:start
Colonel Haruyoshi Nada.

01:07:37.030 --> 01:07:38.764 position:21% line:89% align:start
[KUWAHARA groaning]

01:07:38.798 --> 01:07:40.067 position:35% line:89% align:start
Screw you!

01:07:40.100 --> 01:07:42.136 position:7% line:83% align:start
If you think you can get away
with making enemies out my unit,

01:07:42.169 --> 01:07:43.370 position:5% line:89% align:start
you're in for an ugly surprise!

01:07:43.403 --> 01:07:44.637 position:27% line:89% align:start
[grunts, gasps]

01:07:44.670 --> 01:07:48.741 position:7% line:83% align:start
These micromachines can reach
your cyberbrain in five minutes.

01:07:48.774 --> 01:07:51.111 position:19% line:83% align:start
Then they'll increase
your pain sensitivity.

01:07:51.145 --> 01:07:53.247 position:21% line:83% align:start
Seven-thousand times
what it is now.

01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:57.351 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KUWAHARA]
No, stop! Aaah!

01:07:57.384 --> 01:07:59.052 position:24% line:89% align:start
[KUWAHARA screams]

01:08:19.839 --> 01:08:22.842 position:38% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
She was there!

01:08:25.279 --> 01:08:28.415 position:30% line:89% align:start
[alarm sounds]

01:08:28.448 --> 01:08:29.349 position:33% line:89% align:start
[PAZ grunts]

01:08:29.383 --> 01:08:30.816 position:30% line:89% align:start
[alarm sounds]

01:08:44.198 --> 01:08:46.033 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

01:08:46.066 --> 01:08:47.834 position:27% line:89% align:start
Get in the car!

01:08:51.804 --> 01:08:54.007 position:13% line:83% align:start
[PAZ] The Major's twin and
the East Asian Federation

01:08:54.041 --> 01:08:54.975 position:27% line:89% align:start
were in cahoots.

01:08:55.008 --> 01:08:57.211 position:19% line:83% align:start
I sure wish we'd known
that from the start.

01:08:57.244 --> 01:09:00.113 position:7% line:83% align:start
Guess that rules out a terror
strike on two fronts at least.

01:09:00.147 --> 01:09:02.782 position:21% line:83% align:start
What were you doing
at the embassy anyway?

01:09:02.816 --> 01:09:05.085 position:21% line:83% align:start
I got some data from
that oversized E-paper

01:09:05.118 --> 01:09:06.420 position:24% line:89% align:start
at the bomb site.

01:09:06.453 --> 01:09:10.123 position:16% line:83% align:start
Here, this is what I saw
when I played it back.

01:09:11.925 --> 01:09:14.127 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAZ]
A 3D map of the embassy?

01:09:14.161 --> 01:09:19.233 position:7% line:83% align:start
The PM and his friends were up
to some risky business, huh?

01:09:19.266 --> 01:09:20.467 position:35% line:83% align:start
[KUWAHARA]
The ship was being used for

01:09:20.500 --> 01:09:22.269 position:7% line:89% align:start
domestic espionage activities

01:09:22.302 --> 01:09:24.338 position:21% line:83% align:start
under a secret deal
with the Americans.

01:09:24.371 --> 01:09:27.774 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's not a scandal,
it's a national security issue!

01:09:27.808 --> 01:09:30.978 position:13% line:83% align:start
Then why'd you abandon the
ship just to set up our boss?

01:09:31.011 --> 01:09:32.412 position:19% line:89% align:start
Who is the PM's enemy?

01:09:32.446 --> 01:09:35.182 position:27% line:83% align:start
The PM was using
the Defense Ministry

01:09:35.215 --> 01:09:37.851 position:19% line:83% align:start
to oust the rebels in
the Ministry of Commerce.

01:09:37.884 --> 01:09:40.120 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's all I know, I swear.

01:09:40.153 --> 01:09:43.790 position:13% line:89% align:start
Now please, stop the pain!

01:09:43.824 --> 01:09:46.526 position:21% line:89% align:start
[KUWAHARA screaming]

01:09:50.030 --> 01:09:53.500 position:13% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA] Hm. It was just
a vitamin injection.

01:09:57.537 --> 01:09:59.072 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Uh?

01:10:09.316 --> 01:10:12.019 position:24% line:83% align:start
So he was the real
Colonel Nada all along?

01:10:12.052 --> 01:10:14.154 position:24% line:83% align:start
Maybe his sympathy
for the rank and file

01:10:14.187 --> 01:10:16.423 position:7% line:89% align:start
spawned those false memories.

01:10:16.456 --> 01:10:18.859 position:21% line:83% align:start
Then they preyed on
the guilt in his own mind,

01:10:18.892 --> 01:10:22.195 position:16% line:83% align:start
feelings that drove him
to wear another man's face.

01:10:22.229 --> 01:10:24.464 position:5% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] And they left him alive
as a card to play

01:10:24.498 --> 01:10:26.900 position:21% line:83% align:start
when they wanted to
intimidate the government.

01:10:26.933 --> 01:10:30.203 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Absolutely repulsive.

01:10:30.237 --> 01:10:32.139 position:13% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] And it turns out
Representative Lee

01:10:32.172 --> 01:10:34.474 position:10% line:83% align:start
just nabbed a valuable mine
that used to belong

01:10:34.508 --> 01:10:36.443 position:21% line:89% align:start
to Ambassador Wong.

01:10:36.476 --> 01:10:38.478 position:27% line:83% align:start
In other words,
no matter how they acted,

01:10:38.512 --> 01:10:40.380 position:5% line:89% align:start
they were actually competitors.

01:10:40.414 --> 01:10:44.251 position:19% line:83% align:start
All this mess just so
war merchants can make a dime.

01:10:44.284 --> 01:10:47.087 position:19% line:83% align:start
The PM must have made
a backroom deal with Wong

01:10:47.120 --> 01:10:49.956 position:16% line:83% align:start
in the hopes of getting
Lee out of their hair.

01:10:49.990 --> 01:10:53.260 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA] Lee finds out
and all hell breaks loose.

01:10:53.293 --> 01:10:56.029 position:5% line:83% align:start
Meanwhile, our broker hands out
the virus to both sides

01:10:56.063 --> 01:10:57.632 position:21% line:89% align:start
and laughs about it.

01:10:57.665 --> 01:10:59.533 position:13% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] Probably weighing
them against each other.

01:10:59.566 --> 01:11:01.401 position:33% line:83% align:start
Either way,
one thing's clear now.

01:11:01.435 --> 01:11:05.305 position:10% line:83% align:start
This has been a war between
the PM and the Federation.

01:11:06.473 --> 01:11:09.209 position:30% line:89% align:start
[phone rings]

01:11:12.613 --> 01:11:14.348 position:30% line:89% align:start
Right. Thanks.

01:11:14.381 --> 01:11:17.884 position:10% line:83% align:start
It would seem that someone's
ordered the Major's arrest.

01:11:17.918 --> 01:11:21.054 position:24% line:89% align:start
Leaving, are you?

01:11:21.088 --> 01:11:24.191 position:19% line:83% align:start
Even the Major decided
to go solo on this one.

01:11:24.224 --> 01:11:27.961 position:10% line:83% align:start
You don't have the balls or
the skills to handle this.

01:11:27.994 --> 01:11:29.896 position:5% line:89% align:start
We'll see about that, won't we?

01:11:29.930 --> 01:11:33.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
But in the meantime,
please, keep her safe.

01:11:33.400 --> 01:11:35.068 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Hmph.

01:11:35.102 --> 01:11:36.436 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOGUSA gasps]

01:11:54.421 --> 01:11:57.224 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Major Kusanagi?

01:11:57.257 --> 01:12:00.227 position:13% line:83% align:start
All right, full disclosure
Section 9 told me

01:12:00.260 --> 01:12:02.663 position:27% line:83% align:start
to call them if
you showed up tonight.

01:12:02.697 --> 01:12:05.031 position:24% line:83% align:start
Do I need to keep
this is a secret?

01:12:05.065 --> 01:12:08.536 position:16% line:83% align:start
That will depend on you,
Mister Fujimoto.

01:12:12.540 --> 01:12:14.542 position:27% line:89% align:start
[OSAMU groaning]

01:12:41.268 --> 01:12:42.670 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] You were the one
who brought the bomb

01:12:42.703 --> 01:12:44.171 position:16% line:89% align:start
that killed your father.

01:12:44.204 --> 01:12:46.741 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid there's
no escaping it.

01:12:46.774 --> 01:12:49.075 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
Oh, God.

01:12:49.109 --> 01:12:50.310 position:27% line:89% align:start
One more thing.

01:12:50.343 --> 01:12:52.245 position:21% line:83% align:start
I need to know about
my squad's budget.

01:12:52.279 --> 01:12:54.214 position:19% line:83% align:start
I wasn't able to trace
some of the money.

01:12:54.247 --> 01:12:56.484 position:30% line:83% align:start
Maybe you know
where it came from?

01:12:56.517 --> 01:12:59.252 position:33% line:89% align:start
[OSAMU sobs]

01:12:59.286 --> 01:13:02.122 position:38% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU]
It was military privatization.

01:13:02.155 --> 01:13:05.192 position:21% line:83% align:start
A surplus from when
we broke up Unit 501.

01:13:05.225 --> 01:13:06.059 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:13:06.092 --> 01:13:09.764 position:27% line:83% align:start
[OSAMU] Please,
change my memories back.

01:13:09.797 --> 01:13:13.200 position:5% line:89% align:start
I don't want to live like this.

01:13:13.233 --> 01:13:16.002 position:21% line:89% align:start
It wasn't my fault!

01:13:16.036 --> 01:13:19.005 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] The truth is
a weight we must carry.

01:13:19.039 --> 01:13:21.442 position:24% line:83% align:start
No matter how much
my heart cries out.

01:13:21.476 --> 01:13:24.312 position:24% line:89% align:start
I won't turn away.

01:13:24.345 --> 01:13:26.747 position:33% line:89% align:start
Never again.

01:13:26.781 --> 01:13:28.316 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

01:13:32.787 --> 01:13:34.322 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

01:13:42.296 --> 01:13:43.631 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:13:44.799 --> 01:13:47.167 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
It's remote-controlled!

01:13:54.475 --> 01:13:56.009 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kurutsu!

01:14:25.506 --> 01:14:27.475 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Show me the server floor.

01:15:10.451 --> 01:15:12.320 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
A virus development net.

01:15:12.353 --> 01:15:14.355 position:16% line:89% align:start
Transmitting externally.

01:15:17.758 --> 01:15:19.293 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:15:29.704 --> 01:15:32.340 position:13% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] An attack barrier
and a barrier maze?

01:15:32.373 --> 01:15:35.142 position:21% line:83% align:start
Clearly that info is
something worth protecting.

01:15:35.176 --> 01:15:36.477 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
Your brain associated us

01:15:36.510 --> 01:15:38.245 position:10% line:89% align:start
with our old bodies, I see.

01:15:38.279 --> 01:15:40.748 position:7% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] Sorry,
but we need to restrain you.

01:15:40.781 --> 01:15:41.816 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
On Kurutsu's orders?

01:15:41.849 --> 01:15:44.285 position:16% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
It's our collective will.

01:15:44.318 --> 01:15:46.354 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
Though that does include her.

01:15:46.387 --> 01:15:49.256 position:24% line:89% align:start
Then she is alive.

01:15:49.290 --> 01:15:50.458 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO gasps]

01:15:50.491 --> 01:15:52.460 position:13% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] Please,
you have to stop resisting us.

01:15:52.493 --> 01:15:54.629 position:13% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)] We don't
want to see you get hurt.

01:16:07.575 --> 01:16:08.909 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO gasps]

01:16:17.351 --> 01:16:18.686 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

01:16:20.488 --> 01:16:21.822 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Ugh!

01:16:31.298 --> 01:16:33.634 position:27% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO grunts]

01:16:33.668 --> 01:16:35.336 position:38% line:83% align:start
[IBACHI]
I think that's enough.

01:16:35.369 --> 01:16:38.172 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's not worth it, Kusanagi.

01:16:43.011 --> 01:16:46.313 position:27% line:83% align:start
[RAIZO chuckles]
Just had to come back.

01:16:46.347 --> 01:16:47.983 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:16:48.016 --> 01:16:50.217 position:24% line:83% align:start
--[MOTOKO groans]
--[RAIZO] Ha!

01:16:59.260 --> 01:17:00.594 position:41% line:89% align:start
Move!

01:17:46.674 --> 01:17:50.544 position:21% line:83% align:start
"You have to accept
your limits." Remember?

01:18:02.958 --> 01:18:04.492 position:21% line:89% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO grunts]

01:18:05.359 --> 01:18:06.694 position:19% line:89% align:start
[IBACHI, RAIZO grunt]

01:18:08.029 --> 01:18:09.563 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
Major! [squeals]

01:18:13.334 --> 01:18:15.336 position:16% line:89% align:start
[UNIT MEMBERS groaning]

01:18:30.819 --> 01:18:32.486 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, Sleeping Beauty.

01:18:32.520 --> 01:18:34.856 position:24% line:83% align:start
Had to crack your
secret lab to fix you,

01:18:34.890 --> 01:18:36.958 position:5% line:89% align:start
but I trust you won't complain.

01:18:36.992 --> 01:18:39.728 position:19% line:83% align:start
All those weapon mods
didn't suit you anyway.

01:18:39.761 --> 01:18:43.464 position:7% line:89% align:start
Your body was fine how it was.

01:18:43.497 --> 01:18:45.432 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Why did you do this?

01:18:45.466 --> 01:18:47.636 position:19% line:83% align:start
You wouldn't order me,
as my boss,

01:18:47.669 --> 01:18:49.470 position:19% line:83% align:start
but as a fellow human
with a Ghost,

01:18:49.503 --> 01:18:51.907 position:16% line:83% align:start
you were hoping I'd come
help you out on my own.

01:18:51.940 --> 01:18:53.875 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's what you were
going for, right?

01:18:53.909 --> 01:18:54.810 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Run away.

01:18:54.843 --> 01:18:57.045 position:24% line:83% align:start
As soon as you're
out of the maze, I will.

01:18:57.078 --> 01:19:00.849 position:10% line:83% align:start
But until then, I think I'm
gonna do my own thing.

01:19:10.058 --> 01:19:12.459 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ITO] I hope you'll take
responsibility for this.

01:19:12.493 --> 01:19:13.161 position:30% line:83% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO]
Don't worry.

01:19:13.195 --> 01:19:15.362 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll use my men to clean it up.

01:19:15.396 --> 01:19:16.798 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ROBERT]
I'll have my subsidiaries

01:19:16.832 --> 01:19:18.733 position:27% line:83% align:start
provide you with
soldiers as well.

01:19:18.767 --> 01:19:20.568 position:16% line:89% align:start
Use as many as it takes.

01:19:20.602 --> 01:19:23.138 position:7% line:83% align:start
I can't guarantee any of them
will come back alive.

01:19:23.171 --> 01:19:25.674 position:35% line:83% align:start
This is a
500-billion-dollar business.

01:19:25.707 --> 01:19:26.942 position:13% line:89% align:start
I think can deal with it.

01:19:26.975 --> 01:19:29.410 position:30% line:83% align:start
Your democracy
tricks these idealists

01:19:29.443 --> 01:19:31.378 position:19% line:83% align:start
into thinking they can
change the world.

01:19:31.412 --> 01:19:34.381 position:10% line:83% align:start
And then the majority pounds
them right back into place

01:19:34.415 --> 01:19:35.617 position:10% line:89% align:start
to maintain the status quo.

01:19:35.650 --> 01:19:37.586 position:19% line:89% align:start
[FAKE MOTOKO chuckles]

01:19:52.934 --> 01:19:54.970 position:16% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
You have to stop fighting.

01:19:55.003 --> 01:19:57.672 position:5% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)] We don't
want to see your brain fried.

01:19:57.706 --> 01:19:59.674 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] If you think
my barrier is that cheap,

01:19:59.708 --> 01:20:01.576 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've got a surprise for you.

01:20:07.549 --> 01:20:09.618 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] You
reverse-breached the barrier.

01:20:09.651 --> 01:20:11.620 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
There's no going back now.

01:20:11.653 --> 01:20:13.922 position:27% line:83% align:start
Then help me put
an end to this.

01:20:13.955 --> 01:20:16.625 position:21% line:83% align:start
Where is Kurutsu and
what is her objective?

01:20:16.658 --> 01:20:18.460 position:16% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
Don't know her location.

01:20:18.493 --> 01:20:21.428 position:13% line:83% align:start
Having multiple bodies was
a key part of her strategy.

01:20:21.463 --> 01:20:22.631 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
As for her objective,

01:20:22.664 --> 01:20:23.865 position:24% line:89% align:start
it hasn't changed.

01:20:23.899 --> 01:20:26.768 position:24% line:83% align:start
Survive, no matter
who wins the battle.

01:20:26.801 --> 01:20:28.703 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm sure you're
already aware of this,

01:20:28.737 --> 01:20:31.106 position:7% line:83% align:start
but the East Asian Federation
wants to use dead-ending

01:20:31.139 --> 01:20:34.476 position:30% line:83% align:start
as a means of
monopolizing the market.

01:20:34.509 --> 01:20:35.744 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
There are some children

01:20:35.777 --> 01:20:38.446 position:24% line:83% align:start
who aren't facing
a dead-end yet.

01:20:38.480 --> 01:20:41.016 position:13% line:83% align:start
And what, you're going to
use them as poster children?

01:20:41.049 --> 01:20:43.718 position:5% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)] No. We're
leaving the future to them.

01:20:43.752 --> 01:20:44.853 position:16% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
They will become

01:20:44.886 --> 01:20:45.787 position:19% line:89% align:start
next generation models

01:20:45.820 --> 01:20:48.757 position:24% line:83% align:start
and make long-term
versioning up a reality.

01:20:48.790 --> 01:20:51.526 position:13% line:83% align:start
What makes you think it'll
be any different this time?

01:20:51.559 --> 01:20:53.595 position:7% line:89% align:start
And what about everyone else?

01:20:53.628 --> 01:20:54.963 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

01:21:22.757 --> 01:21:24.759 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIERS yelling]

01:21:28.763 --> 01:21:33.768 position:21% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA A gasping]
Why, you!

01:21:44.579 --> 01:21:45.080 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER U gasps]

01:21:45.113 --> 01:21:46.648 position:24% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER T grunts]

01:22:05.567 --> 01:22:07.969 position:10% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT/RIGHT)]
You were always free.

01:22:08.003 --> 01:22:10.171 position:7% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)] You're
always searching for a future.

01:22:10.205 --> 01:22:13.008 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
If only we could be the same.

01:22:13.041 --> 01:22:15.277 position:10% line:89% align:start
You two were protecting me.

01:22:15.311 --> 01:22:16.211 position:16% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (RIGHT)]
Our brains have reached

01:22:16.245 --> 01:22:18.113 position:16% line:89% align:start
their limit, either way.

01:22:18.146 --> 01:22:21.283 position:7% line:83% align:start
We'll shift to the Third World
before they expire.

01:22:21.317 --> 01:22:22.717 position:19% line:83% align:start
[YOUNG TSUMUGI (LEFT)]
Pray that we may become

01:22:22.751 --> 01:22:25.553 position:16% line:89% align:start
part of the sea of data.

01:22:25.587 --> 01:22:27.088 position:19% line:83% align:start
[TSUMUGI (LEFT/RIGHT)]
Perhaps, someday

01:22:27.122 --> 01:22:29.991 position:21% line:83% align:start
someone will be born
who can access you.

01:22:34.029 --> 01:22:35.563 position:30% line:89% align:start
[MOTOKO gasps]

01:22:56.684 --> 01:22:58.287 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Found it!

01:22:58.320 --> 01:23:00.021 position:21% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIER V groaning]

01:23:00.055 --> 01:23:02.891 position:21% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIERS screaming]

01:23:04.260 --> 01:23:05.794 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ROBERT growls]

01:23:20.708 --> 01:23:22.278 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAZ]
Ah!

01:23:22.311 --> 01:23:25.880 position:27% line:89% align:start
[IBACHI grunts]

01:23:25.914 --> 01:23:27.916 position:33% line:89% align:start
[PAZ groans]

01:23:33.955 --> 01:23:34.722 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
Saito!

01:23:34.756 --> 01:23:36.758 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SAITO]
I am gonna kill that guy!

01:23:36.791 --> 01:23:39.161 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU groans]

01:23:39.195 --> 01:23:41.197 position:16% line:89% align:start
[BATOU, RAIZO grunting]

01:23:45.900 --> 01:23:47.369 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Everybody alive out there?!

01:23:47.403 --> 01:23:50.106 position:7% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6B] We can't repair
you if you're dead!

01:23:50.139 --> 01:23:53.409 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
I told you, studs don't die.

01:23:53.442 --> 01:23:54.642 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU grunts]

01:23:54.676 --> 01:23:55.377 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:23:55.411 --> 01:23:56.945 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU groans]

01:24:02.451 --> 01:24:03.985 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ISHIKAWA gasps]

01:24:07.256 --> 01:24:09.258 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ISHIKAWA groans]

01:24:13.429 --> 01:24:15.998 position:24% line:83% align:start
[ARMORED SOLDIER]
Huh?! Ah!

01:24:16.031 --> 01:24:19.034 position:21% line:89% align:start
[SOLDIERS screaming]

01:24:22.871 --> 01:24:24.140 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
You just gonna stand there?

01:24:24.173 --> 01:24:27.409 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you can't deliver,
I'll replace you.

01:24:27.443 --> 01:24:28.611 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ISHIKAWA]
Hmph.

01:24:28.643 --> 01:24:31.347 position:13% line:83% align:start
Hey, it's not my fault you
interrupted me, Gorilla Woman.

01:24:31.380 --> 01:24:33.915 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU yells]

01:24:35.384 --> 01:24:37.919 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:24:39.121 --> 01:24:40.655 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU snarls]

01:24:42.958 --> 01:24:43.459 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BATOU grunts]

01:24:43.492 --> 01:24:45.027 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO growls]

01:24:49.098 --> 01:24:53.735 position:19% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO, IBACHI grunt]

01:24:53.768 --> 01:24:56.338 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

01:24:56.372 --> 01:24:57.907 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:24:59.475 --> 01:25:01.010 position:41% line:83% align:start
[PAZ]
Major!

01:25:03.445 --> 01:25:05.214 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO growls]

01:25:12.321 --> 01:25:14.323 position:10% line:89% align:start
You traitor, I'll kill you!

01:25:19.962 --> 01:25:21.964 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:25:35.978 --> 01:25:37.980 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOGUSA]
Major! You all right?

01:25:39.348 --> 01:25:41.050 position:30% line:89% align:start
[BORMA grunts]

01:25:46.021 --> 01:25:47.022 position:30% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunts]

01:25:48.490 --> 01:25:51.493 position:27% line:89% align:start
[RAIZO grunting]

01:26:03.505 --> 01:26:06.475 position:24% line:83% align:start
[BATOU] I told ya,
your old parts are the best.

01:26:06.508 --> 01:26:08.544 position:10% line:89% align:start
And I told you to run away.

01:26:08.577 --> 01:26:10.946 position:10% line:89% align:start
Bunch of adrenaline junkies.

01:26:10.980 --> 01:26:15.017 position:5% line:83% align:start
Parts like you would be a lot of
trouble to replace, you know.

01:26:17.052 --> 01:26:20.789 position:19% line:83% align:start
There's still one more
job we gotta take care of.

01:26:28.163 --> 01:26:30.432 position:16% line:83% align:start
[AMAGATA] What good will
arresting me do?

01:26:30.466 --> 01:26:32.301 position:24% line:83% align:start
The same game will
start up again

01:26:32.334 --> 01:26:34.503 position:35% line:83% align:start
after this
administration dissolves.

01:26:34.536 --> 01:26:36.972 position:27% line:83% align:start
You know, every
minister that retired today

01:26:37.006 --> 01:26:39.308 position:13% line:83% align:start
said the exact same thing,
and I don't give a damn.

01:26:39.341 --> 01:26:41.377 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AMAGATA] It's the corrupt
system that's to blame.

01:26:41.410 --> 01:26:44.213 position:10% line:83% align:start
