her personality.

01:28:48.370 --> 01:28:51.173 position:21% line:89% align:start
I can't explain it.

01:28:51.206 --> 01:28:53.275 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] How long have
you been doing this?

01:28:53.308 --> 01:28:54.711 position:24% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS (KURUTSU)]
Since the beginning.

01:28:54.744 --> 01:28:58.448 position:16% line:83% align:start
I've compensated for my
shortcomings with micromachines,

01:28:58.481 --> 01:29:01.383 position:16% line:83% align:start
and although I can't be
prosthetized myself,

01:29:01.418 --> 01:29:04.253 position:21% line:83% align:start
I have operated many
prosthetic bodies.

01:29:04.286 --> 01:29:06.388 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yours was the only name
I couldn't take.

01:29:06.423 --> 01:29:08.123 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
What about Fire-Starter?

01:29:08.157 --> 01:29:11.160 position:19% line:83% align:start
Were you the developer
all this time?

01:29:22.439 --> 01:29:24.306 position:13% line:83% align:start
[CHRIS (KURUTSU)] One day
you'll see that the diversity

01:29:24.339 --> 01:29:27.142 position:30% line:83% align:start
of information
packages is endless.

01:29:27.176 --> 01:29:31.079 position:16% line:83% align:start
That they can give birth
to a new world.

01:29:31.113 --> 01:29:36.084 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm going there now,
everyone else is waiting for me.

01:30:08.150 --> 01:30:11.253 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KURUTSU] I pity you,
one who was once so free,

01:30:11.287 --> 01:30:15.492 position:27% line:83% align:start
trapped in this
miserable, waking world.

01:30:43.653 --> 01:30:47.590 position:10% line:83% align:start
I trust you were able to say
goodbye before she moved on?

01:30:47.624 --> 01:30:51.093 position:13% line:83% align:start
How could you have allowed
this all these years?

01:30:51.126 --> 01:30:52.462 position:21% line:89% align:start
Because we had hope,

01:30:52.495 --> 01:30:54.264 position:5% line:89% align:start
two hopes to avert the dead-end

01:30:54.297 --> 01:30:56.833 position:24% line:83% align:start
of cyberbrains and
prosthetic bodies.

01:30:56.866 --> 01:30:59.235 position:21% line:83% align:start
It was either going
to be her or you.

01:30:59.269 --> 01:31:01.838 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's that simple.

01:31:01.871 --> 01:31:04.139 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Take him away.

01:31:06.809 --> 01:31:07.844 position:33% line:83% align:start
[CARETAKER]
You should stop searching

01:31:07.877 --> 01:31:09.679 position:13% line:89% align:start
for the names of the dead.

01:31:09.712 --> 01:31:11.648 position:7% line:89% align:start
There's nothing to be gained.

01:31:11.681 --> 01:31:15.618 position:5% line:83% align:start
Take it from someone who's long
been a dead man himself.

01:31:20.189 --> 01:31:21.157 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
What is it?

01:31:21.190 --> 01:31:22.659 position:13% line:89% align:start
Can you take us with you?

01:31:22.692 --> 01:31:24.727 position:5% line:89% align:start
Where are we supposed to go now?

01:31:24.761 --> 01:31:25.862 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
That depends on you.

01:31:25.895 --> 01:31:27.830 position:19% line:89% align:start
[BOYS and GIRLS gasp]

01:31:27.864 --> 01:31:29.499 position:27% line:83% align:start
Are you willing
to sell your Ghost

01:31:29.532 --> 01:31:31.701 position:21% line:83% align:start
for the sake of some
uniform standard?

01:31:31.734 --> 01:31:35.605 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sacrificing those less
fortunate than you are?

01:31:35.638 --> 01:31:37.340 position:27% line:83% align:start
You've all been
given cyberbrains,

01:31:37.373 --> 01:31:39.509 position:21% line:83% align:start
and Ghosts to guide
your actions.

01:31:39.542 --> 01:31:41.377 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you want something
from others,

01:31:41.411 --> 01:31:44.447 position:13% line:83% align:start
you have to find something
to offer in return.

01:31:45.848 --> 01:31:48.418 position:24% line:89% align:start
Build your future.

01:31:57.393 --> 01:31:59.729 position:5% line:83% align:start
[ITO] It's only the government's
"official position."

01:31:59.762 --> 01:32:01.831 position:24% line:83% align:start
It won't interfere
with our trade.

01:32:01.864 --> 01:32:02.799 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ROBERT]
Good.

01:32:02.832 --> 01:32:05.602 position:21% line:83% align:start
I would hate to see
the aristocracy starve

01:32:05.635 --> 01:32:08.438 position:24% line:83% align:start
because the slave
nation fails to serve.

01:32:08.471 --> 01:32:10.540 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ITO] Well, the slave trade
always benefits

01:32:10.573 --> 01:32:12.342 position:19% line:89% align:start
from labor shortages.

01:32:14.277 --> 01:32:16.279 position:19% line:83% align:start
--[HOTEL STAFF] Huh?!
--[HOTEL GUESTS gasps]

01:32:30.760 --> 01:32:32.762 position:38% line:83% align:start
[BATOU]
You really gonna do this, Major?

01:32:43.974 --> 01:32:46.175 position:21% line:89% align:start
[BODYGUARD gasping]

01:32:48.911 --> 01:32:51.414 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] I see our Far East
trade representative,

01:32:51.447 --> 01:32:54.751 position:7% line:83% align:start
the Vice-Minister of Commerce,
and a number of union officials.

01:32:54.784 --> 01:32:56.285 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ROBERT]
How dare you!

01:32:56.319 --> 01:32:57.887 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
The Ministry of Foreign Affairs

01:32:57.920 --> 01:33:00.189 position:19% line:83% align:start
and the Defense Agency
are watching this,

01:33:00.223 --> 01:33:02.925 position:7% line:83% align:start
and I'm sure Vice-Minister Ito
here would be happy

01:33:02.960 --> 01:33:05.361 position:21% line:83% align:start
to testify about the
PM's assassination.

01:33:05.395 --> 01:33:06.529 position:41% line:83% align:start
[ITO]
I'm ruined.

01:33:06.562 --> 01:33:07.497 position:33% line:89% align:start
Impossible.

01:33:07.530 --> 01:33:09.933 position:19% line:83% align:start
He applied for asylum
and it was granted.

01:33:09.967 --> 01:33:11.935 position:21% line:83% align:start
All the papers were
signed, as well.

01:33:11.969 --> 01:33:13.037 position:35% line:89% align:start
Prove it.

01:33:13.070 --> 01:33:16.205 position:21% line:83% align:start
Show some patience.
The papers are at the embassy.

01:33:16.239 --> 01:33:18.541 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll forward them to you later.

01:33:18.574 --> 01:33:20.777 position:19% line:83% align:start
People are still loyal
to the old PM.

01:33:20.810 --> 01:33:22.412 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't think they won't kill you.

01:33:22.445 --> 01:33:26.416 position:21% line:83% align:start
[ROBERT] Ha! In this
civilized nation of pacifists?

01:33:26.449 --> 01:33:28.451 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Oh, are we?

01:33:34.657 --> 01:33:36.359 position:10% line:89% align:start
They're outside the window!

01:33:39.963 --> 01:33:41.664 position:41% line:83% align:start
[ITO]
Ah! Help me!

01:33:41.698 --> 01:33:43.700 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Hold your fire!

01:35:49.026 --> 01:35:52.029 position:19% line:83% align:start
Sure is nice to watch
the cherry blossoms together.

01:35:52.062 --> 01:35:54.363 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
This is an assignment.

01:35:54.397 --> 01:35:56.767 position:27% line:83% align:start
Twenty-four hour
cherry blossom surveillance.

01:36:02.438 --> 01:36:03.707 position:35% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI]
Got a job, for you Major.

01:36:03.740 --> 01:36:05.474 position:24% line:83% align:start
In South Niihama,
District 4, they've---

01:36:05.508 --> 01:36:06.710 position:33% line:89% align:start
No, thanks.

01:36:06.743 --> 01:36:09.980 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ARAMAKI] I got your budget,
so get to work.

01:36:10.013 --> 01:36:11.380 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
Logicoma!

01:36:11.414 --> 01:36:12.616 position:30% line:83% align:start
[LOGICOMA 6A]
It's true!

01:36:12.649 --> 01:36:15.819 position:7% line:83% align:start
Budget approval forms checked,
confirmed and looking good!

01:36:15.853 --> 01:36:16.687 position:38% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO]
All right, then.

01:36:16.720 --> 01:36:18.822 position:13% line:89% align:start
Flower stakeout suspended!

01:36:20.958 --> 01:36:22.659 position:33% line:89% align:start
Get moving!

01:36:26.864 --> 01:36:28.732 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MOTOKO] You're the best
